title: torte
directions: Beat 4 eggs in pan; add brown sugar and butter.
Stir constantly until hot.
Remove from heat and add flour and baking powder.
Beat again with spoon.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased pan (13 x 9-inch) at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar, butter and egg yolks together until soft.
Add flour, milk, cocoa, walnuts, coconut and baking powder.
Beat at high speed for about 2 minutes, then add egg whites.
Beat again for another 2 minutes.
Put in a greased pan (8 x 8-inch); bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: In medium bowl, mix first 9 ingredients, 1 tablespoon water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
On waxed paper with hands, roll half of meat mixture into a 12-inch long roll.
Repeat with other half. Cut each into 4 pieces.
In 12-inch skillet, over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook meat rolls until browned on all sides.
Remove.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Cook pork roast and vegetables on stove in saucepan covered with water over medium heat for 3 hours.
Strain veggies and pork. Reserve veggies.
Take bone out of pork roast and shred with a fork.
Trim fat.
Put pork, veggies, salsa and barbecue sauce back in pot and simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice or on rolls.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix together; store in airtight container.
Use 3 teaspoons per cup.
Add boiling water.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 1/3 cup of the mixture per cup of hot water.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; after mixed well form into balls.
(If dry, add more peanut butter.)
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: orange blossom muffins
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil, juice and water.
Add sifted biscuit mix.
Stir in marmalade.
Grease small muffin pans; fill 2/3 full. Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: zelzenicia
directions: Bake in greased 9 x 13 inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes till set.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in cool whip. Chill over night.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given. Mix well.
Put into loaf pan and bake at 350°.
Bread is done when top springs back to touch.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain fat.
Open pinto beans and corn.
Drain about half the juice from the corn.
Add corn and pinto beans to the pot.
Add the hamburger meat to the pot.
Add the stewed tomatoes.
Cut up the onion and bell pepper, then add to the pot.
Fix the elbow noodles; drain the water and add to the pot.

title: corn bread
directions: Put small amount of grease in cast-iron skillet at 350° until hot.
Mix ingredients and place in skillet.
Bake in oven at 450° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Beat egg.
Add mayonnaise and broken bread slices.
Beat well. Add salt, peppers, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard.
Mix in crab meat.
Make into cakes and fry until brown.

title: overnight slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, green pepper, onion, olives and salt in large bowl.
Mix well and set aside.
Combine vinegar, oil, mustard, sugar and celery seed in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour dressing over vegetables, tossing lightly.
Chill overnight.

title: salsa salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed.
Let cool.
Punch holes (with straw) all over the top of cake.
Mix milk and butterscotch sauce in a bowl.
Pour over top of cake after it cools.
Then put Cool Whip over cake.
Chop Heath bars and spread over cake. Refrigerate.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Mix jellos and boiling water; let jell in refrigerator.
Mix jello, fruit and 1 package miniature marshmallows with juice.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 8 ounces Cool Whip and 1 cup mayonnaise. Spread over jello.
Garnish with pecan pieces or grated sharp cheese.
Chill several hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Season squash and rice while cooking.
Mix all ingredients together and place in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbling, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: congealed mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Reserve juices.
Add enough water to juices to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Dissolve gelatin in hot tea.
Add 1 1/2 cups liquid and chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in fruit and water chestnuts.
Put in mold and chill.
Before serving, make dressing.
Combine mayonnaise, whipping cream, rind, sugar and mace.
When ready to serve, put one bed of lettuce and garnish with carrot strips.
Put the dressing in center.

title: new garlic bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut bread in 1/2 lengthwise; put cut side up on foil lined cookie sheet.
In medium size skillet, heat oil until hot; add onion and garlic.
Cook stir until tender, 4 to 5 minutes.
Add spinach and heat until warm (1 minute).
Remove from heat; stir in Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning and mix well.
Spread spinach mixture evenly over bread halves.
Sprinkle with tomato, Mozzarella cheese and basil.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Cut into slices.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix well with mixer.
Pour on top of the first.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Mix first 3 items in a large bowl and set aside.
In a saucepan, mix pineapple juice, sugar, flour, vinegar and egg.
Cook until thick.
Let cool.
Mix Cool Whip into mixture.
Add to apple mixture; stir in peanuts. Garnish top with peanuts.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, rice, 1/4 cup of water, chopped onion, seasoned salt, garlic powder, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
If mixture seems dry add enough water to form into balls.
Shape mixture into any size ball.
Smaller balls will cook faster. Place shallow level of oil into a 10 to 12 inch skillet.
Cook over medium heat, browning meatballs on all sides.
When done, drain off excess oil.
Meatballs should be browned evenly with a bit of crunchiness to them.
This will soften in the simmering phase but leave bits flavoring the tomato paste.
Take can of tomato paste and paint over each ball with a spoon or knife in the same pan.
Take approximately 1/2 cup of water and pour over pasted meatballs.
Cover and simmer on low for 20 to 30 minutes. Occasionally turn the meatballs thoroughly coating with paste. This will make a tomato gravy.
If too thick, add more water sparingly.
If too thin, leave cover off and continue to simmer. Serves 4 to 6.

title: souper deluxe hot dish mix
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Last 1/2 hour, cover with crushed potato chips.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and then add the milk and slightly beaten egg yolks and stir well.
Cook until thickened and stir constantly so it won't stick to the bottom of the pan.
Fold in 3/4 cup moist shredded coconut just before you fill the baked pie shell.
Sprinkle whip cream or meringue topping with 1/4 cup coconut.

title: cocoa-cinnamon pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Sift flour, salt, baking powder, cocoa and cinnamon together.
Mix in dry ingredients, alternating with small amounts of milk. Add vanilla.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan and flour lightly. Spoon in batter.

title: sweet minglers candy mix
directions: In a large microwave-safe bowl, melt chocolate at high for 1 minute or until chocolate is melted.
Stir in and mix peanut butter and peanuts.
Gently stir Kellogg's Crispix cereal into chocolate-peanut butter mixture, until well coated.
Place confectioners sugar in a 2-gallon storage bag.
Add coated cereal to sugar and close bag.
Gently shake cereal mixture until well coated.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Makes 8 cups.

title: coyote caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients except cream cheese, eggs, green onions and salsa.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Spread cream cheese on round serving plate.
Spoon bean mixture evenly over cream cheese. Arrange eggs on bean mixture around edges along with salsa. Sprinkle with green onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 12.

title: puff pastry danish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put 1 cup flour into bowl.
Cut in butter; sprinkle with 2 tablespoons water and mix with fork.
Mix into a ball and divide in half.
Pat and roll dough into 2 (12 x 3-inch) strips.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.

title: stacy keach's baked chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel potatoes and onions; cut into round slices.
Place on bottom of baking dish.
Cover entire bottom, making a second layer and layering onions over taters. Place chicken breasts over the onions and potatoes.
Cover lightly with safflower oil.
Sprinkle lightly with pepper, parsley and oregano.
Cover entire dish with stewed tomatoes.
Bake 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: michigan rocks(christmas cookies)
directions: Mix ingredients together as listed.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook, bone and dice the chicken.
Place uncooked rice in bottom of a flat 8 x 12-inch pan.
Put diced chicken on top of rice.
Mix soups and water together and pour over rice and chicken. Top with crushed potato chips and slices of margarine. Bake in a 325° oven for 2 hours.

title: mexican casserole dish
directions: Cook meat in skillet until done.
Add salt, pepper and garlic. Add green chili peppers, onions and beans.
Quarter soft tortillas and spread in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Pour meat mixture over tortillas.
Cover with a layer of cheese, then another layer of soft tortillas.
Add sour cream and soup, then another layer of cheese.
Dry fry remainder of tortillas and eat as chips with casserole.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, beaten eggs, vanilla and butter. Fold in nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: snack pizza
directions: Let kids roll out their own biscuit dough and put Ragu Pizza Sauce on dough.
Then they may add grated cheese and any other toppings they like, such as mushrooms or sausage.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: heath bars
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with foil and place saltines in pan. Boil brown sugar and margarine for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and bake for 5 minutes at 400°.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate bits and spread until smooth, then sprinkle on nuts.
Keep in cool place.
Break apart when completely cooled.

title: cheerio surprise
directions: In saucepan or in microwave, heat the brown sugar and corn syrup until dissolved.
Add the peanut butter; stir until well mixed and melted.
Pour in cereal; stir until Cheerios are evenly coated.
Press into an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Cool until firm, then cut in squares.

title: old fashioned blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar and egg, slightly beaten. Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to milk.
Add blueberries. Combine all ingredients.
Fill tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: party dip
directions: Mix together and add clam liquid, if needed.
This may be served warm or cold with crackers or toast squares.

title: hungry boys casserole
directions: Saute ground beef, celery and onion in large skillet. Add water, tomato sauce, salt, paprika and monosodium glutamate. Add pork and beans. Simmer while preparing your favorite biscuit recipe; don't bake. Put meat mixture into 12 x 8-inch or 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with biscuits. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes until biscuits are golden brown. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: june's taco casserole
directions: Chop onion and cook with meat.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning; use a little less water in sauce so it's less juicy.

title: corn chowder
directions: Break up meat and saute with onion.
Remove and reserve. Cook milk at low temperature with potatoes and bay leaf for 20 minutes, or until potatoes are done (watch to keep from scorching).
Add salt, pepper and corn, then sausage.
Serve hot. Excellent with corn bread.

title: "oil pastry"
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Pour salad oil and cold water into measuring cup (do not stir).
Add all at once to the flour mixture.
Stir lightly with a fork.
Form into 2 balls; flatten dough slightly.
Roll each between two 12-inch squares of waxed paper.
When dough is rolled in a circle to edges of paper, it will be right thickness for crust.
Peel off top sheet of waxed paper and fit dough, paper side up, into pie plate.
Remove paper. Makes enough pastry for one 8 or 9-inch double-crust pie.

title: lazy oven stew
directions: In large casserole, mix together tomato sauce, tapioca, water with bouillon dissolved in it, wine, beef stew meat (cubed), salt and pepper.
Cut up potatoes, carrots, onions and celery; add to other ingredients and mix well.
Cook in 250° oven for 4 to 4 1/2 hours.
Keep covered during cooking time.

title: cocoa peanut logs
directions: Melt bits and peanut butter and add Cocoa Krispies.
Stir until coated.
Lightly butter a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Press mixture into pan.
(Do not cook.)

title: crabmeat pinwheels
directions: Mix by hand the first 5 ingredients.
Take mixture and spread 3/4 of a tortilla with it.
Roll up tightly and secure with a toothpick.
Finish out the rest of the tortillas this way and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Slice to desired thickness and skewer with party pick.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake.
Prepare pudding mix with milk.
Layer ingredients in large punch bowl.
Begin with 1/2 can pie filling, add layer of cake (crumbled), 1 banana, 1/2 can pineapple and 1/2 of prepared pudding; repeat layers.
Ice with Cool Whip.
Decorate with fresh strawberries.

title: pecan pie surprise
directions: Grease bottom and side of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Reserve 2/3 cup cake mix for filling.
In large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, butter and egg.
Mix until moist.
Press into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until light golden brown.
Meanwhile, prepare filling.
Pour over partially baked crust.
Sprinkle with 1 cup chopped pecans.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add pineapple and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until done at 375°.

title: smoked oyster dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill. Serve with crackers or chips.

title: marinade(chicken)
directions: Mix ingredients well; cover and chill.

title: chicken delight
directions: Combine all ingredients in a baking dish (greased).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with biscuits made from scratch or Bisquick or refrigerator type (your choice). Return to oven at 400° and cook for 12 to 15 minutes, until biscuits are brown.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Grease loaf pan. Mix well and put in loaf pan. Cook at 325° for 1 hour.

title: eggs with potatoes and shrimp
directions: Boil the potatoes.
After boiled, drain and cut each one in half.
With a spoon, make hole on each half of potato big enough to fit a boiled egg inside.
After you have made all the holes, put the boiled egg between 2 halves of potato and close the potatoes. Put the potatoes in a baking pan.

title: cocoa pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa together.
Add eggs, milk and butter.
Pour into 8-inch pie crust.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Use egg whites for icing.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Stir in pecans.
Drop dough by level tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool slightly on cookie sheet.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Then combine in crock-pot with all other ingredients.
Cook for 4 hours on medium.
Delicious.

title: pig roast potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Bake 1 cup of sesame seed for 1 hour at 300° to toast.
Add brown sugar, oleo, vanilla and egg; mix well.
Gradually add sifted flour, salt, baking powder and sesame seed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheets.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature.
Finger in 1/2 package diced beef, scallions and Worcestershire sauce.
Mold into ball and roll in the rest of diced beef.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill about 1 hour. Makes 6 cups.

title: pork chops
directions: Spread mustard on both sides of chops.
Dip in flour.
Fry until brown.
Add chicken noodle soup and simmer until tender.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all together and beat for 4 minutes.
Pour into 3 small greased and floured bread tins (7 3/8 x 3 5/8 x 2 1/4-inch).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli oriental
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain; keep warm.
Combine butter, sugar, soy sauce and 1 tablespoon water. Heat until butter melts.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with seed.

title: fresh strawberry butter
directions: In a food processor or medium size bowl with electric mixer, beat strawberries until pureed.
Beat into butter (mixture should have a few small pieces of fruit in it).
Beat in sugar and pack into serving bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: scandinavian sugared nuts
directions: In shallow pan, arrange nuts and 2 teaspoons butter.
Bake in a 350° oven, stirring often, for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: low-fat, no salt, chicken with beans
directions: Cook the meat until no longer raw in a heavy pot over medium heat.
Stir while cooking to break it up in small pieces and keep from burning.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook another two minutes while stirring gently.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer five minutes.
Serve over brown rice.
This is delicious.
I make it often.

title: beef chuck boiled dinner
directions: In electric frying pan, scorch meat on both sides.
Keep meat in middle of pan and add water until pan is 3/4 full.
Put cabbage in far corners.
Carrots and potatoes in middle.
Cover for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until done.

title: sweet-meat sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in glass container.
Keep refrigerated.
Delicious with meat.

title: neiman marcus bars
directions: Mix together yellow cake mix, 1 egg, butter and 1 cup chopped pecans for the first layer and put in 9 X 13 inch greased and floured pan.
Mix powdered sugar, 2 eggs, coconut, cream cheese and vanilla, and spread second layer over the first mixture.
Bake 10 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped pecans on top and bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top when you take out of 350 degree oven.
For a variation, use 1 box of butter fudge cake mix.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine 1/2 beef with the rest of the ingredients.
Mix thoroughly, then roll ball in remaining beef.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together well with mixer.
Pour into greased dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until fairly firm.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Cut cake crosswise into 3 layers.
Combine sour cream, pineapple, coconut and brown sugar.
Place bottom layer of cake on serving platter.
Top with 1/3 of the pineapple mixture.
Add second layer of cake.
Top with another 1/3 of the mixture.
Add final cake layer and top with remaining pineapple mixture.
Top with mandarin oranges.
Chill.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Blend in butter with a pastry knife until the mixture has the consistency of meal.
Add raisins, eggs and buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly and turn out onto a floured work surface.
Knead lightly 12 times.
Lightly flour 2 (8-inch) round cake pans.
Divide mixture in half, pressing half of the dough into each cake tin.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake until golden brown (approximately 45 minutes).

title: novelle green's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix and bake for 40 minutes.

title: beef-mac casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add onion and garlic; cook until tender.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and turn into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine pumpkin, oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Gradually add sifted flour, soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Add nuts. Bake in 3 loaf pans for 1 1/2 hours or until done at 350°.
Spray pans with Pam before baking.

title: best ever chocolate cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients. Add the water, oil, vinegar and vanilla. Beat on low speed for 1 minute. Beat on medium for 1 minute. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool.

title: chili sauce
directions: Chop fine or use food processor on all veggies. Skin tomatoes. Put all ingredients in canning kettle and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until thick. Jar and seal.

title: *peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients; form into balls.
Over a double boiler pan, melt the chocolate and wax.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture.
Drop on wax paper one at a time, then refrigerate.
Makes 3 or 4 dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Cut franks into bite size.
Place into 2-quart baking dish.
Mix together all other ingredients except bacon.
Arrange bacon slices on top of beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add soups.
Starting with hamburger mixture, layer casserole dish with alternating hamburger and Tater Tots.
End with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until brown.

title: bacon and egg brunch
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. (Fill all the spaces.)
Fry bacon and break into pieces.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon on bread.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Pour over bread and sprinkle salt on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake the next day for 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: mexican dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook hamburg.
Prepare taco seasoning mix as directed on back, then add to hamburg.
Spread softened cream cheese in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Layer the next ingredients, starting with hamburg mix, then onions, peppers, tomatoes and salsa.
Top off with cheeses.
Bake for 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips

title: rachel kalberer's spinach pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add cream cheese and sour cream; beat.
Add melted butter, cottage cheese and spinach; beat.
Fold in cheese (add 1 to 2 tablespoons flour if cottage cheese is watery).
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Use greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ingredients with your hands. Spread in pan and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs,
sugar,
milk
and
salt together; add corn. Melt margarine in pan and pour mixture in.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Cook and drain noodles. Set aside. Brown meat. Add green peppers and onions. Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water and seasoning.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer half the noodles, meat sauce and Velveeta cheese. Repeat. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ensenada crepes
directions: Slice cheese into 1/2 inch strips.
Cut green chili peppers into 1/4 inch strips.
Place a slice of ham on each tortilla.
Put 1 strip of jack cheese in center of ham slice with a slice of chili pepper.
Roll and secure with a toothpick.
Place rolls, slightly apart in a greased 9 x 13 baking pan.
In a sauce pan, melt butter and slowly add flour, stirring constantly.
Add milk and cheese, cooking until cheese is melted.
Add salsa, mustard, salt and pepper.
Stir together.
Pour over tortillas. Sprinkle some paprika over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 5 layer salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients.
Mix together the mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread mixture over fourth layer.
Top with cheese. Refrigerate.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Set aside.
Mix milk, sugar, salt and shortening until dissolved.
Add 2 cups flour; beat.
Add yeast.
Gradually add 4 cups flour.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in bowl 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix both contents in a large mixing bowl (on medium speed) for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Refrigerate if wanted to be served cool. (Better served after mixing.)
Dip apples, bananas and oranges. The apples are very good with this.
The dip, after mixing, should be real creamy.

title: tuna rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine soup, water and onions in saucepan and bring to boil.
Set aside.

title: bake-me-not peanut bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine butter, peanut butter, flour and vanilla.
Beat with an electric mixer until smooth.
In a saucepan, cook sugar and water over medium heat to hard boil stage (250° on candy thermometer).
Pour slowly over butter/flour mixture.
Beat until thickened and well blended.
Add peanuts and pour into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into bars. (Looks and tastes a lot like peanut butter fudge, but these really are cookies.)

title: cooked mushrooms(great with beef)
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cooking wine and mushrooms.
Add garlic salt, Texas Pete and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: cheese delight
directions: Put all ingredients in baking dish; place in oven at 350° until cheese melts.
Stir several times.
Place in refrigerator to cool. This is good for sandwiches or served on vegetables such as asparagus or broccoli.

title: betsy's grapes
directions: Pull most grapes off stem; leave some on for decoration. Wash, dry and chill.

title: baked crab salad
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients (except crumbs for top).
Put in baking dish; sprinkle 1/2 cup crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Heat 1 cup milk and butter.
Dissolve sugar, cocoa and salt in remaining 1/2 cup milk.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Pour mixture into hot milk and butter.
Cook until stiff, using double boiler.
Pour into already baked pie shell.
Top with meringue made with egg whites, well beaten and sweetened to taste.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Combine pineapple juice, 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour, soda, salt and eggs in a bowl.
Mix 3 minutes with a spoon.
Grease and line an 8 x 12-inch pan with 2 thicknesses of waxed paper.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Turn out on rack.
Combine remaining sugar, butter and milk in a heavy saucepan; bring to a boil.
Stir once.
Boil for 4 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Let cool. Beat until desired spreading.
Frost cake.
Chill before serving.

title: dill sauce for broiled fish
directions: Combine all and serve over your favorite broiled fish.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients for dressing.
Combine tuna and cucumbers.
Just before serving, toss tuna and dressing.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal crunchies(cookies)
directions: Cream the shortening or margarine with brown sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and milk.
Add flour, soda and salt, blending well to make a thick batter.
Fold in oats, pecans and raisins or chopped dates.
Drop by teaspoonful 3-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes or until lightly golden. Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg, 1/3 cup peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oats.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven. Remove from oven and sprinkle with a few semi-sweet morsels. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll the ingredients in pecans and form a ball.

title: chocolate peanut butter pizza
directions: Beat oleo and peanut butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds in a medium mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 cup of flour, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Beat until mixture is thoroughly combined.
Beat or stir in remaining flour. Press down evenly into a 12 or 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and chocolate chips. Bake with marshmallows until they are puffy.
Sprinkle with candy coated chocolate pieces.
Cool; cut into wedges.

title: donna mae's spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, sift together flour, sugar and spices.
Cut in lard or shortening like you would for pie dough.
Add rest of ingredients; beat well.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or two 8 or 9-inch layer pans.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter until light. Add sugar and continue creaming until fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.

Mix in flour, soda and salt, then remaining ingredients. Drop from a teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheets, spacing cookies about 2-inches apart, and bake 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned. Remove and cool on wire racks.
Makes about 5 dozen.
Contains 100 calories per cookie.

title: tuna bun sandwiches
directions: Combine ingredients, mix lightly. Split buns and fill with mix. Put cheese on top. Put buns in aluminum foil and place in slow oven at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Chunk and parboil chicken about 5 minutes; drain and set aside.
Spray baking dish with Pam and set aside.
In a bowl, mix cranberry sauce, Wish-Bone dressing and onion soup mix.
Place chicken in prepared dish.
Spoon cranberry mixture over chicken using all of mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes; bake covered until last 30 minutes.

title: mom's best cake(pound cake)
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat in vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cranberry wine punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat 1 or 2 hours on low.
(A crock-pot is great for this.)

title: green enchiladas
directions: Heat soup, milk and Velveeta cheese in double boiler until cheese is melted. Add chilies and pimentos. Brown meat. Combine grated Longhorn cheese and onion. Fill each tortilla with cheese/onion mixture. Roll lightly and place in baking dish. Pour cheese sauce over the enchiladas. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: Saute onion in margarine; cool.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli pasta salad
directions: Cook vermicelli.
Drain and cool.
Mix in all other ingredients and let set overnight, covered, in refrigerator.

title: breakfast before
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Put in bottom.
Next add bread, eggs and cheese on top.
Cover and let set overnight in refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate layered dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour and pecans and spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Pour on cooled crust.
Mix chocolate pudding, vanilla pudding and 3 cups cold milk and pour over cream cheese layer.
Top with remainder of Cool Whip and grated Hershey or chocolate sprinkles.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in three layers at 350° until done.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into jello in a large bowl. Stir 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened (consistency of unbeaten egg whites).
Stir in Cool Whip with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut. Spoon into 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Unmold.
Makes 10 servings.

title: brutzel bars(tastes like heath bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a standard size cookie sheet with built-up sides of aluminum foil.
Lightly spray the foil with Pam. Arrange saltine crackers single layer over foil
Set aside.
In medium saucepan, combine butter and sugar and cook to a "Brutzel" boil.
As soon as it reaches a bubbling boil, remove from heat and gently pour over crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and rearrange any crackers that have moved around.
Scatter the milk chocolate chips over top.
Spread evenly with knife to cover crackers.
Cook and refrigerate a few hours.
Remove about 15 minutes before serving.
Break into bite-size pieces.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Bake at 350° until brown.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into pieces.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and garlic powder.
Add minced garlic; fill empty jar with water and add to mixture, then add parsley.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, until golden brown.
Stir and cook again until golden brown.

title: grilled turkey, cheese and tomato sandwiches
directions: Spread each bread slice on one side with butter.
Arrange 1 slice turkey, 1/2 slice cheese and 2 tomato slices on 4 of the buttered sides.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with remaining 4 slices of bread, buttered sides in . Beat eggs with milk, salt and cayenne in shallow dish.
Melt the 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet or griddle.
Dip sandwiches in egg mixture to coat both sides, using a flat spatula.
Brown sandwiches in butter, turning to brown both sides and melt the cheese.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: sweet potato casserole(mrs. bass said this goes well with ham loaf.)
directions: Mix and place in baking dish.

title: lindsay's "forget the cookies just give me that batter" chocolate
directions: In small pan, melt butter.
While hot, add both sugars.
Let cool.
Meantime, mix flour, soda and salt in mixing bowl.
In small bowl, beat egg slightly.
Add egg and vanilla to butter mixture; stir.
Add butter mixture to flour mixture; stir.
Add chocolate chips and walnuts; stir all until well mixed. Refrigerate for about an hour.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Do not greased pan or cookie sheet.
Roll mixture into walnut-sized balls; place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Cookies should be moist and chewy.
Yum!

title: canned vinegar green beans
directions: Add salt, vinegar and sugar to beans.
Pressure in cooker 15 minutes at 10 pounds of pressure.

title: pagach
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water. Pour 1/2 cup scalded milk on butter and sugar. Cool to lukewarm. Add dissolved yeast. Sift flour and salt into bowl. Add eggs and yeast mixture with remaining milk and water. Knead well. Cover. Let stand in warm place until double in bulk (about 2 hours). Turn out on floured surface. Divide in 3 parts. Cover each portion with a bowl. Let rest about 10 minutes. Roll out one part at a time. Turn over, flatten center with back of hand, filling with potatoes and cheese or fried sauerkraut. Draw up ends and pinch together. Can fill center, fold over and pinch around "open" edges. Brush with melted butter. Bake at 375°.

title: easy-veggie dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Best made the day before used.

title: leggy dip
directions: Mix cheeses in blender at medium speed until well blended. Shred sea legs by tearing.
Stir chopped onion and pepper sauce into cheese mixture.
Add sea legs and mix.
Into 9-inch baking dish, spoon mixture.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes until lightly browned at 350°.
Makes 2 cups.

title: banana slush
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients to cooled sugar water in 5 quart container.
Freeze in 2 or 3 equal containers.
Remove several hours before serving (mixture should be slushy).
Pour into punch bowl and add ginger ale in proportion to amount of frozen punch used.

title: quick summer pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and sour cream.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add Cool Whip last.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Can be topped with small can of crushed pineapple, drained, and nuts or any other pie filling desired.

title: rice custard
directions: Beat together the sugar, milk, eggs, flavorings, salt and nutmeg.
Put in casserole dish.
Add rice and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until set.

title: american chop suey
directions: Saute beef, green pepper, onion and garlic in 5-quart nonstick saucepan until beef is browned.
Add mushrooms, sauce, salt, pepper, oregano and macaroni (cooked).
Cover; simmer under low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate sauce for ice cream or cream puffs
directions: Heat cocoa and sugar until hot.
Add rest of ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Boil exactly 3 minutes.
Cool.

title: apple pie
directions: Slice apples into enough water to cover them.
Drain off water.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in a saucepan and add apples.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly. Pour into prepared pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 40 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: In a frypan, saute onion in margarine.
Add brown sugar, salt, pepper and bread pieces.
Add tomatoes; chop up some.
Pour into a shallow baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry walnut delite
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar and margarine.
Blend into fine crumbs; add walnuts and mix well.
Set aside 1 cup of mixture. Bake 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: thelma's just right cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, mix flour, sugars, soda and salt.
Add shortening, egg, milk and vanilla.
Stir with wooden spoon until well mixed or mix with your hands.
Stir in cereal, coconut and chocolate pieces.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 10 minutes.

title: mixer meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs until frothy in large mixer bowl.
Reduce to lowest speed and add tomato puree and water.
Tear bread into pieces and gradually drop in mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Add onion and seasoning.
Slowly add beef.
If mixture gets too thick before all of beef is added, add some water, a little at a time.
Shape into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/4 hours. Serves 15.

title: whole wheat bread(my first housekeeping venture.)
directions: Sprinkle dry yeast into warm water to which brown sugar has been added.
Put in large bowl.
Scald milk; pour in bread bowl and add hot water, sugar or honey, butter, salt and molasses. When lukewarm, add yeast mixture, then whole wheat flour and unbleached flour.
Mix until smooth and knead about 10 minutes.

title: good dressing (stuffing)
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in oil.
Mix with remaining ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Shape into balls around marshmallows.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Dip in egg white; coat with cornflake crumbs.
Place in greased baking dish. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients and add wet ingredients.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: hamburger roll
directions: Fry hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Put in soup (no water).
Mix Jiffy mix with milk, just enough to make it stay together.
Roll out oblong.
Put hamburger down through the middle and fold over the sides.
Bake until done, about 15 minutes.
Make gravy and pour over it when you eat it.

title: divinity
directions: Cook until it starts to boil; cover for 2 minutes.
Uncover and cook until it spins a long thread; let stand until it quits bubbling.
Pour over 2 egg whites stiffly beaten.
Add flavoring and nuts; beat until it will drop from a spoon and stand in peaks.

title: pastry recipe (meat pie)
directions: Work lard in flour with pastry blender.
Then add suet and work in thoroughly.
Add water to make a soft dough just a little more moist than ordinary pastry dough.
Divide dough in 4 parts.

title: pickled beets
directions: Select young, tender, sweet beets.
Trim off tops, leaving 1-inch of stem.
Leave stem and top root to prevent bleeding and loss of color.
Wash thoroughly.
Cover with boiling water and cook until done (when fork slips in easily).
Remove skins and roots.
Small beets may be left whole.
Place beets in mixture of sugar and vinegar.
Bring to boil.
Place in pint jars.
Add allspice to each pint jar.
Be sure liquid covers beets.
Seal with new lids and rings that have been in boiling water.

title: ultimate chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend oatmeal in blender until powdery. Cream butter, blend in sugar and brown sugar.
Mix in oatmeal, baking soda, baking powder, salt and 1-1/4 cups of the flour.
Add Hershey bar and chocolate chips.
Add 2 eggs and only the yolk of the third egg.
Add vanilla.
Slowly add last 1/2 cup of flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Form into balls using a cookie dough scoop. Place 3-4 inches apart on cookie sheet sprayed with non-stick spray.
Bake 8-12 minutes.
Let cookies cool on cookie sheet for several minutes until firm.
Remove and cool on rack.

title: chicken fruit salad
directions: Combine chicken, apples, pineapple chunks, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Stir in almonds.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve on lettuce or endive.
Makes 6 servings.

title: white chocolate salties(candy)
directions: Combine chocolate and shortening in double boiler.
Cook until chocolate melts.
Pour into a large bowl.
Stir in pretzels and nuts.
Spread onto buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Chill about 20 minutes or until firm.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and eggs.
(Add soda to applesauce and let stand.)
Beat in dry ingredients, then add applesauce, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 300° for about 1 1/4 hours in a tube pan.

title: split pea soup
directions: Wash split green peas and add to 2 quarts boiling water.
Add diced vegetables.
Cover pot and simmer on low temperature about 1 hour.
Add ham pieces.
Simmer about another 30 minutes.
Peas should look mushy.
Soup will need to be stirred occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and put into casserole dish. Top with crushed Fritos. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spiced cranberry sauce
directions: Tie cinnamon, cloves and allspice in gauze bag; boil in salted water with cranberries for 23 minutes.
Add sugar; cook 2 minutes longer.

title: italian style chicken breasts
directions: Dip chicken breasts in eggs, then crumb mixture.
To make the crumb mixture, combine the bread crumbs and the Parmesan cheese. Microwave in 1 1/2-quart casserole, loosely covered, with wax paper, for 5 minutes.
Turn over and cover with sauce.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chip dip
directions: Put chopped onion in blender; blend until crushed.
Add drained tomatoes; blend together (about 2 seconds).
Put in large bowl.
Add all other ingredients.
Great also as a sauce on tacos, burritos, etc.

title: life's recipe
directions: Mix thoroughly and add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy for others to taste.
Fold in 4 cups prayer and faith to lighten other ingredients and improve texture.
After pouring mixture into your daily life, bake well and slowly with the heat of human kindness. Serve with a smile.

title: trash
directions: Melt butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter in a large heavy pan on low heat.
Pour the cereal into another large pan and pour the melted mixture over the cereal.
Stir.
Put 1/2 of the box of 10x sugar into a small trash bag.
Pour the cereal mixture over top of this mixture.
Pour the remaining half of the 10x sugar over it and shake well.

title: lemon flavored cheesecake
directions: Roll graham crackers into crumbs; next is optional, add 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 stick melted oleo to graham crackers crumbs (save calories and fat just use graham crackers.)
Set these aside; make jello with 1 cup of boiling water only!
Set aside.
Whip can milk until airy, add sugar and cream cheese, blend until smooth.
Then fold in lemon jello.
Pour into graham crackers that were placed in full size 9 x 11-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle the top with a few graham cracker crumbs.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix together.
Then add yeast mix.
Beat eggs and mix with other ingredients.
Add vegetable oil and stir in good.
Stir while adding flour.
Mix well and knead good.
(Better if add 3 cups flour at a time.
Knead after each addition.)
Roll out on a floured surface.
Knead well.
Put in a bowl and put in refrigerator; let rise.
Take out what you want at a time and make into rolls or bread and leave the remainder in the refrigerator or take out and make into your favorite yeast rolls.
Bake at 450° until done.
For a glazed shiny look you can beat (slightly) an egg white and brush on top of the bread.

title: deviled salmon
directions: Mix milk and bacon fat; cook until thick.
Add this sauce to salmon.
Add salt, pepper and boiled eggs and mix.
Pour into baking dish, cover with mashed potatoes and brown.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it comes to a boil. Boil 2 minutes longer.
Lower heat and put in package of Jell-O.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
Wash and drain strawberries and cut in halves.
Put strawberries in pie shell. Pour mixture over strawberries. Chill. Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
(Pie can be made the day before, then topped with cream before serving.)

title: triple chocolate surprise crock-pot cake
directions: Spray crock-pot with nonstick cooking spray. Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a bowl (DO NOT BEAT). Pour into crock-pot; cover and let cook on low for about 6 hours.

title: cauliflower with tomato cheese sauce
directions: Remove green leaves from cauliflower.
Cut off any bruised or dirty spots.
Soak in bowl of cold salted water for 30 minutes. Cook, uncovered, in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Add salt to water just before cooking is completed.
Drain.
Saute garlic in butter.
Add soup and cheese.
Cook over low heat until well mixed. Serve over cauliflower.
Yields 6 servings.

title: caramel strata
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and butter until sugar is melted.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Place 12 slices of bread (trim crust) on top, 6 then 6 on top or 6 Texas toast slices.
Mix eggs, milk and vanilla; pour over bread.
Let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until golden brown.
Invert when served.
Can add nuts to syrup if desired.

title: german sweet bread
directions: Mix dates, boiling water and soda.
Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add date mixture and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over batter before baking.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: grilled corn in the husk
directions: Prepare grill.
Carefully peel back the husks on each ear of corn, but do not detach.
Remove and discard silk.
Rub each ear of corn with 1/2 tablespoon butter and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Pull the husks back up around the corn and tie them snugly at the top with heavy kitchen string.
Arrange corn on grill.
Grill. Turn frequently until the husks are blackened in spots, about 12 minutes.
Cut off the string.
Remove husks and serve immediately.

title: ree's double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl and add pudding mix.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk. Mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate about 4 hours before serving.

title: ralph jr.'s muskrat
directions: Brown onion in frying pan with bacon grease.
Salt, sage and pepper muskrat, then flour.
Add muskrat to onion, frying until brown.
Pour in chicken broth and let simmer until tender.

title: granola mix
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a large bowl, combine oats, wheat germ, coconut, sunflower seeds, sesame seeds and nuts.
Blend well. In a large saucepan combine brown sugar, water, oil, honey, molasses, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Heat until sugar is dissolved, but do not boil.
Pour syrup over dry ingredients and stir until well coated.
Spread into 5 (13 x 9-inch) baking pans or cookie sheets with sides.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Bake 15 minutes longer for crunchier texture.
Cool. Add raisins or other dried fruit.
Put in airtight containers. Label and store in cool, dry place.
Use within 6 months.
Makes 20 cups.

title: punch
directions: Mix well the Kool-Aid and 2 quarts of water.
Mix all ingredients well.
Chill, then serve.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together in a large saucepan. Add chipped ham.
Saute together celery, onion and ground beef.
Drain and add to ham mixture. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: raisin applesauce muffins
directions: Beat
together	eggs,
oil
and applesauce.
Add flour, baking soda,
baking
powder and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins. Spoon batter
into	muffin pans and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes
or
until muffins are firm to the touch and browned. Walnuts may be added when adding raisins.

title: mommy gnecco's chicken soup for colds and flu
directions: Variation for day after Thanksgiving:
Substitute turkey carcass for chicken.

title: super beefy enchiladas
directions: Combine beef, 1/2 cup cheese and onion; set aside.
Combine soup and enchilada sauce.
Dip tortillas in hot oil to soften a few seconds on each side.
Top each tortilla with one heaping tablespoon of meat mixture; roll up.

title: potato cake
directions: Mix ingredients together well, saving juice of raisins.
Use juice to get proper consistency for cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: catfish parmesan(yield: 3-4 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 450°.

title: cinnamon puffs
directions: Place 1 tablespoon butter in a bowl.
Microwave 30 seconds. Stir in biscuit mix, sugar, nutmeg, egg and milk.
Beat 30 seconds. Place paper liners in cupcake holder or custard cup.
Fill each one 1/2 full.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes, turning 1/4 turn every 30 seconds.
Let cool 2 to 3 minutes.
Place remaining butter in a small bowl and microwave 30 seconds.
Mix in sugar and cinnamon.
Dip warm puffs into batter and then into sugar mixture.
Serve warm.

title: microwave quickie fudge
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in a bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Remove bowl; stir ingredients to mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Add nuts; mix.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish and place in freezer 20 minutes or in refrigerator 1 hour.
Yields 1 pound.

title: asparagus-spaghetti toss
directions: Cook spaghetti and asparagus separately according to package directions; drain.
Toss spaghetti with basil, thyme and onion powder.
Add asparagus, tomatoes, salad dressing and lemon juice. Serve warm or cover and refrigerate for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sour cream corn muffins
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs, sour cream and butter.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.

title: best ever enchiladas
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain.
Add flour and seasonings; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in tomatoes; cook until thoroughly heated.

title: meat or chicken stock
directions: Put bones (or carcass) and water in stockpot and bring to boil; lower heat and simmer for 2 hours, skimming as necessary. Add remaining ingredients and cook for 2 more hours. If using cooked bones, add all ingredients at once, bring to boil, skim, then simmer for 2 hours. Strain, cool, cover and refrigerate.

title: mints
directions: Mix well.
Mixture will be stiff.
Make into balls and mash with a fork.
Dip in granulated sugar.
Lay on wax paper to dry; turn and dry other side.
Store in airtight container when dry.

title: grandma's toffee bars
directions: Mix together oatmeal, sugar, syrup and shortening.
Pat out the first layer on a large cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Melt chips and peanut butter.
Spread on top.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Add yeast to water.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix. Roll out dough as you would for regular biscuits.
Dip in butter and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Dough can be kept in the refrigerator in covered bowl for 3 days.

title: honey bee cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat butter, sugar, honey and egg until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set and light brown around edges, 7 to 9 minutes.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheet onto a wire rack to cool. Makes 36 cookies.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice in 3 cups water; drain.
Cook bacon in wok over medium heat; stir often.
Drain.
Remove drippings.
Beat eggs into wok with drippings; spread over bottom.
Cook until set, 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove.
Roll up and cut into thin strips.
Repeat twice.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Chop vegetables; place in large container.
Add salt and let stand 24 hours.
Drain in colander and wash.
Heat sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and turmeric to a boil; pour over vegetables and simmer for 10 minutes.
Dip into hot jars and seal.

title: twice cooked divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt in small saucepan; cover and boil
for
minutes.	Uncover
and
cook
to 248°. Meanwhile, beat the
egg
whites
in a large bowl until stiff, but not dry.
Pour
of syrup over egg whites, beating all the time.
Put	remaining
syrup on to cook to 272° and slowly pour over
the
candy,
still
beating constantly.
Beat until mixture begins to lose its gloss and stands in peaks (approximately 7 minutes).
Mix
in	vanilla
and
nuts;
drop by teaspoons on waxed
paper.
Store in airtight containers.
Makes about 4 dozen pieces.

title: summer squash bake
directions: Place squash and water in a 1 1/2 quart microwave-safe bowl. Cover and microwave on high for 4 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain well.
Stir in green pepper, onion, pecans, mayonnaise, 1/3 cup of cheese, sugar, salt and pepper.
Transfer to a lightly greased shallow 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Makes 6 servings.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Boil cabbage for 5 minutes in salted water.
Mix well all ingredients and wrap in wilted cabbage leaves.
Put in a baking dish and cover with tomato juice and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: hamburger frito pie
directions: Brown beef with onion in skillet.
Mix Ro-Tel and cheese soup together.
Spoon beef mixture over Fritos.
Top with cheese sauce.

title: extra yummy chocolate pudding cake
directions: In an oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) mix brown sugar and cocoa. Then stir in water, cut large marshmallows into quarters or use the mini and scatter over this mixture.
Spoon over devil's food cake batter (prepared according to mix directions).
Top with nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or as hot fudge sundae cake.

title: crunchy chicken salad in phyllo cups
directions: Brush 2 miniature muffin pans with 1 tablespoon melted butter; set aside.
Place 1 sheet of phyllo on a damp towel (keep remaining phyllo covered).
Lightly brush phyllo with melted butter.
Layer remaining 4 sheets of phyllo on first sheet, brushing each sheet with melted butter.
Cut stack into 24 (2 1/2-inch) circles.
Place phyllo circles into prepared muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Let cool completely in pans on a wire rack.
Remove from pans.

title: scalloped eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant; cut in 1-inch cubes.
Cook in boiling salted water for 8 minutes.
Drain.
Add egg, milk, butter, onion and crumbs.
Stir mixture; pour into square pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus and eggs
directions: Arrange half of the asparagus spears in bottom of greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with slices of egg, salt and pepper and sprinkle with cheese.
Spoon in half of the white sauce or soup; repeat layers and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine potatoes, milk, eggs and sugar.
Beat at high speed. Add flavorings.
Mix baking powder with 1 teaspoon milk and add to potato mixture.
Pour into 2 unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix butter, sugar and salt.
Cook for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add soda.
Coat popcorn with mixture.

title: apple butter in crock-pot
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in crock-pot.
Turn on high until it starts bubbling.
Turn on low; cook overnight or all day.

title: fruit cocktail sheet cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; add fruit cocktail and mix a little. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan.
Spread coconut on cake.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: kolachky*(kolaczki)
directions: Heat milk to boiling point. Add to cold potato water. Crush 2 yeast cakes into this liquid. Add 1 cup flour; beat until smooth and let rise 1/2 hour. Add remaining flour, sugar, salt and butter; knead very thoroughly until dough forms soft ball. Cover and let rise until double its bulk, about 2 hours. Roll out on floured board until dough is 1-inch thick. Cut into 2-inch squares. Fill squares with fruit filling (prunes, dates, apricots or cottage cheese). Pinch corners of squares together, being certain fruit is completely enclosed in square. Place in buttered pans and let rise 1 hour. Brush tops with melted butter and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until nice and brown.

title: pecan chicken
directions: Preheat broiler and set broiler rack at second level from heat. Grind pecans and bread crumbs together until fine.
Dip each piece of chicken into the breading, coating both sides.
Pan-fry chicken on each side for 1 minute in oil.
Transfer breaded chicken to broiler pan and broil for 2 minutes per side.
Serves 4. 190 calories. 7.1 g. total fat (5.5 sat).

title: pea salad
directions: Defrost frozen peas in microwave for approximately 1 minute. Be careful not to overheat.
Prepare lettuce as for a salad. Starting with lettuce, begin layering ingredients, depending on the size of the bowl you use, you may have one or two layers of each ingredient.
Top with Miracle Whip salad dressing just before serving.

title: diet soup
directions: Wash and chop celery.
Put in a large pot; cover with water and boil until tender.
Add onions, green pepper, cabbage and V-8 juice; bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until all vegetables are tender, approximately 2 to 3 hours.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and salt to yeast mixture.
Then add all ingredients together and mix.
Pinch off the amount you want to bake.
Make biscuits and turn in greased pan.
Put the remaining dough in refrigerator to be used as you wish.
It will keep a long time.
Bake as usual.

title: "grand dragon" rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water; set aside, while mixing other ingredients.
Be sure yeast is thoroughly dissolved.
Mix together dry ingredients; add remainder of warm water and oil to make a soft dough.
Set aside, covered, at room temperature for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: oriental spinach salad
directions: In salad bowl, blend vinegar, soy sauce, sugar and ginger. Stir in oil and onion.
Add spinach, cabbage and sesame seed. Toss lightly to coat.
If desired, serve in cabbage leaf lined bowl.
Serve at once.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: clay's christmas hot buttered rum
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar.
Add ice cream and spices.
Put in Tupperware with lid and refreeze.
For each mug, take 2 tablespoons of batter, 2 ounces rum and add boiling water to fill.

title: crab stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well, dry thoroughly. Put in oven and bake at 325° until you can pierce with fork. Cut the potatoes lengthwise and scoop out potatoes and whip with butter, cream, salt, pepper, onion and cheese. With a fork
mix in crab meat and refill the potato shells. Sprinkle with paprika and reheat in very hot oven about 15 minutes. These freeze nicely.

title: honey glazed baked ham
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place ham, fat side up, on rack in roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer in thickest part.
Bake, uncovered, 2 hours.

title: irish creme liquor
directions: Put everything in a blender and mix well.
Put into bottles. Keep in fridge.
Can be poured over slivered ice.
Don't keep over 30 days.

title: vegetables parmesan
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Over medium-high heat, cook zucchini, onions and garlic until crisp, then discard garlic and place zucchini and onions in bowl.
Heat another 2 tablespoons oil in same Dutch oven.
Stir in broccoli and cauliflower.
Add water, cover and cook until tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.
Return zucchini and onion to pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Cook 5 minutes or until hot. Makes 6 servings; contains 285 calories per serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle package of taco seasoning mix on top of cheese mixture.
Spread bottle of salsa on next.
Chop peppers and place on top of salsa.
Sprinkle 1 package shredded Cheddar cheese on top of salsa.
Dice tomatoes and place on top of cheese.
Shred lettuce and layer on top. Refrigerate and serve with nachos.

title: banana walnut bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and milk.
Add the dry ingredients, flavoring and bananas.
Mix well, then add nuts. Spray loaf pan with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° until done.
Takes a long time to bake.
Keep testing with a toothpick after 1 hour. Freeze ripe bananas, then thaw.
Makes the bread better and bananas easier to mash.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil spaghetti.
Drain and rinse in cold water and set aside.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Beat well.
Sift together next 3 ingredients.
Add alternately to the first mixture with the lemon juice, milk and rind.
Pour mixture into a loaf pan.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix by package directions.
Pour 1/2 in greased oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk and butter, stirring constantly.
Pour over cake.
Sprinkle 1 cup nuts and chips over this.
Pour remaining batter over filling. Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Bake 20 minutes longer.

title: barbecue pork and beef sandwiches(for crock-pot)
directions: About 8 1/2 hours before serving, combine all ingredients. Cover and cook on high for 8 hours.
With wire whisk stir mixture until meat is shredded.
(Serve on long hard rolls.)

title: mexican pepper dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: seafood tossed salad
directions: Tear lettuce in bite size pieces.
Slice and quarter tomatoes. Pull apart crab meat.
Slice cucumbers and onions thin.
Toss all ingredients together and serve chilled.

title: turkey or chicken souffle
directions: Melt shortening; blend in flour, pepper and salt.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add cheese, egg yolks, turkey or chicken and parsley; then add bread crumbs.
Beat egg whites until stiff and they form peaks.
Fold turkey or chicken mixture in your egg whites.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle the butter with bread crumbs and then add your meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 35 minutes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat butter until melted. Add soups and onion.
Mix well; add sour cream.
Pour over potatoes.
Put crushed corn flakes or crushed potato chips on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat pudding and milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place a layer of graham crackers in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of pudding mixture, layer of crackers, rest of pudding and top with crackers.
Chill for a little while.
Top with frosting. Refrigerate.

title: baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Salt and pepper it.
Roll in flour and leave plenty of flour on it.
Place in a baking pan.

title: mom's pizza chicken
directions: Place in 2-quart utility dish with meaty pieces to outside and bony pieces in center.
Mix together next 6 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cook for 20 to 24 minutes on High power.
Rotate 1/4 turn half-way through cooking time.
Evenly sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over chicken.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Return to oven for 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Rest 10 minutes.

title: lemon salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Cool.
Add ginger ale and chill until partially thickened.
Fold in marshmallows, bananas and pineapple.
Turn into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and chill until firm. Cover with topping.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain.
Put back in pot.
Add 2 sticks margarine and 2 packages cream cheese.
Stir until melted and blend well.
Put in oblong baking dish.
Use spinach pot to melt 1 stick margarine and stir in box of stuffing mix and seasonings. Spoon over spinach.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 1/2 hour.

title: edwina's hushpuppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add just enough buttermilk to form a stiff batter.
Drop by small spoonfuls into hot oil until golden brown.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil and mix with rest of ingredients.
Pour in a deep pie crust shell.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour in a greased and floured loaf pan. Pour 1/2 cup melted butter over dough. Bake in 400° oven for
40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli for 5 minutes and drain.
Mix the soup, egg, mayonnaise and onion.
Place broccoli in greased casserole.
Pour mixture over it and sprinkle the crumbled cheese crackers over the top.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: In Dutch oven, cook ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, kidney beans, tomato sauce, chili powder, basil, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. (I don't like chunks of whole tomatoes, so I put them in a blender.
More or less chili powder according to taste.
I let cook longer than the 20 minutes.)

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients together; salt and pepper to taste.
Bake until brown on top and cheese is melted.

title: brownie cup cakes
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo.
Mix together eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Add to the chocolate and oleo.
Add nuts.
Beat together and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer each ingredient in order given, sprinkling 2 tablespoons of sugar over mayonnaise layer.
Refrigerate in airtight container overnight.
Toss when served.

title: carrot and zucchini muffins
directions: * If you wish to use all-purpose flour which is not self-rising, add 2 1/2 teaspoons baking powder and 3/4 teaspoon salt to flour mixture.

title: oriental chicken and noodles
directions: In small bowl, stir together cornstarch, broth and soy sauce until smooth; set aside.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain off most liquid.
Set aside.

title: tomato bake
directions: Mix crackers, cheese and onion in a well-greased casserole dish.
Mix sugar, salt and tomatoes; pour over cheese mixture and dot with butter or margarine.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add orange peel, eggs and milk. Mix baking powder into flour.
Add a little at a time, stirring well between additions.
Drop by teaspoon full onto cookie sheet. Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: low-fat spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach, drain and squeeze until dry.
Stir dry soup before measuring to mix evenly.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve with raw vegetables or slices of French or sourdough bread.

title: hamburger and biscuit dinner
directions: Spread hamburger in baking dish.
Add seasonings.
Pour milk over to cover; may need more milk.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with biscuits and bake 10 minutes or until biscuits are browned in oven at 375°.

title: lite chocolate eclair
directions: Blend pudding mix and milk with electric mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Beginning with graham crackers, layer with pudding mixture the graham crackers.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Ice with chocolate icing.

title: chicken pie
directions: Take chicken off bone and cut up into small pieces. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: italian tomato salad
directions: Cut the tomatoes into bite size pieces.
Place in a medium bowl.
Cut 6 basil leaves into small pieces.
Slice the onion and add to tomatoes.
Salt to taste.
Sprinkle on oregano and olive oil.
Stir everything together.
Eat with Italian bread.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix brown sugar, oil and egg and then add sour milk.
Add soda, salt and vanilla and add flour and then rhubarb.
Grease loaf pan; pour in mixture.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and butter together.
Sprinkle on top of bread before baking. Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry bread
directions: In bowl, stir thawed berries, eggs and oil.
In large bowl, combine all dry ingredients and nuts.
Add berry mixture.
Stir just until blended.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Contains 195 calories per 1/2-inch slice.

title: rolled broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place one roll on cookie sheet, flatten out, place the piece of broccoli in center of roll.
Sprinkle with cheese and roll closed.
Brush with butter to seal and glaze.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix your seasonings in Hellmann's mayonnaise.
I use garlic, a little mustard, onion powder and grated onion.
Cut up boiled eggs.
Mix all together.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Put salt pork in skillet and fry until meat is crisp.
Add onions and cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Add to potatoes and corn and cook for about 10 minutes.
Add milk, salt, pepper and parsley.
Bring to boiling point and add butter.
When melted, serve.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Whip heavy cream until soft peaks form.
Fold in sour cream and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; blend lightly.
Chill well.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Break brownies into small pieces and place in bottom of bowl. Add layer of pudding then layer Cool Whip. Repeat, ending with Cool Whip on top. Crumble favorite candy bar (Hershey, Butterfinger and Heath bar, etc.). Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together sugar and syrup. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes until it is light brown.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend well.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda and stir gently until light and foamy.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet (spray).
Cool 1/2 hour.
Break into pieces.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and water.
Set aside.
Cook sausage.
Cool to room temperature.
Add cheese.
Mix with Bisquick mixture and make into small balls.
Bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: smothered fried chicken
directions: Place chicken, milk and red pepper seasoning in bowl. Refrigerate, covered, for 2 hours.
Combine flour, pepper and salt in a shallow plate.
Drain chicken.
Discard any remaining milk mixture.
Coat chicken with flour.
Working in batches, brown chicken in hot oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Return all chicken to skillet.
Lower heat to medium-low and cook covered for 20 minutes, turning once.
Increase heat to medium-high, uncover and cook 5 minutes to crisp skin.
Drain chicken on brown paper bags.

title: mexican pizza supreme
directions: Use prepared crust from frozen food section or prepare your own.
Spread beans on cooked crust.
Spread pizza sauce on top of beans.
Add oregano, chili powder, salt and pepper to hamburger during cooking.
Sprinkle hamburger and cheeses over top of pizza. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Have tomatoes, lettuce and onions ready to sprinkle on top of pizza when done.

title: dump cake
directions: Combine pineapple, eggs, vanilla, flour and baking soda.
Beat for 2 minutes. Add coconut and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Bake in oven for 45 minutes at 350°. Ice with favorite frosting.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Line quiche pan with tortillas, overlapping on bottom and turning up to cover sides.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove the crust from the oven and sprinkle 2 ounces cheese over crust. Meanwhile, spray skillet with Pam and saute onion and red pepper. Add turkey sausage and cook until done.
Add spices and chilies. Mix well.
Remove from heat and add eggs.
Pour sausage mixture into crust.
Sprinkle remaining 2 ounces of cheese on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Quiche can be frozen after it is cooked.
To reheat, thaw and heat at 350° until heated through, about 20 minutes.

title: pasta and cheese
directions: Cook shells as directed on box; drain.
Layer in baking dish in order:
sauce, shells, sour cream, Provolone, sauce.
Last layer, place slices with Mozzarella.
Cover and cook.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: mud turtles
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 2 minutes (no longer). Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop on wax paper and let cool.

title: savory appetizer franks
directions: Mix in saucepan.
Simmer over low heat; simmer for 10 minutes. Add hot dogs and heat for 15 minutes longer.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Combine well and cook by spoonfuls in hot cooking oil in a skillet, turning once when nicely browned.
Drain well on paper towels or brown paper bag.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cut cheese into chunks. Melt cheese in crock-pot, then add remaining ingredients. Serve with chips. Yummy!

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Melt and pour over casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
In small bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and bananas.
Pour evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or
until lightly browned.
Cool.
Chill.
Cut into bars.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: "easy" chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend cake mix, oil, water and eggs.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
The tops of the cookies will look pale.

title: drop molasses cookies (gingersnaps)
directions: Mix together flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, ginger and salt; set aside.
Mix cooled margarine and sugar; blend until smooth.
Add eggs and molasses.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Separate the chicken wing drumsticks from the wing tips.
Deep fry the chicken in medium-hot (380°) peanut oil for 5 to 8 minutes; drain on paper towels.
Melt the butter in a large frying pan.
Add the Tabasco and vinegar.
Roll the chicken wings around in the mixture to coat them.
Serve with Blue cheese dip and celery sticks.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: jackpot drop cookies
directions: Measure sifted flour. Sift flour again with the soda and baking powder and set aside.
Put margarine, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla in a medium mixing bowl.
Beat thoroughly. Add flour mixture and mix well. Add rolled oats and chocolate chips and/or raisins. Stir until mixed.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet about 2-inches apart. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: sweet and sour coleslaw
directions: Chop cabbage, bell pepper and onions.
Stir in sugar and set aside.
Bring to
a boil oil, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: dutch pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Set a 10-inch heavy skillet with heat resistant handle over low heat.
Melt butter in skillet.
Tilt pan to coat sides and bottom.
Sift together flour, sugar and salt. Beat eggs and milk together.
Stirring constantly, blend egg mixture into flour mixture.
Quickly pour batter into hot skillet. Cook 2 to 3 minutes over medium heat.
Place pan in oven and bake at 425° for about 10 minutes or until pancake is light golden brown and top springs back when touched.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix and store airtight.
Mix 1/4 cup of mix with hot water.

title: easy christmas mints
directions: Melt almond bark until creamy.
Smash peppermints in Baggie with hammer.
(Food chopper makes them very fine and turns recipe pink.)
Combine and pour onto cookie sheet.
Place in refrigerator until hard.
Break into small pieces.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and put half of the crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cream cheese and butter until smooth with a mixer.
Fold in powdered sugar, then the whipped topping.
In a separate bowl, mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Fold cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture together; pour into pan with the cookie crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over the top.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan over medium heat.
Stir frequently, will scorch easily.
Bring to a boil. Allow to boil for 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla; mix well.
Drop with teaspoon onto wax paper. Allow to cool about 1 hour and enjoy!

title: ice cream
directions: Mix together; put in ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix gelatin in boiling water until dissolved.
