Add pineapple and pour into large, greased Bundt pan.
Red cherries may be placed in bottom to look like wreath.
Allow to set.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine, sugars, vanilla and eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: exquisite shrimp
directions: Remove shells and veins.
Discard veins, but save shells! Put shells, liquid, pepper, bay leaf and pinch of salt in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Strain through sieve; discard shells.
If there is more than 1 1/2 cups liquid, boil down to that volume.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in top of double boiler over flame.
Blend in flour and add 1 1/2 cups liquid, stirring constantly.
Continue stirring until sauce thickens.
Place over simmering water and cover.
Heat 3 to 4 tablespoons butter in skillet and add peeled shrimp which have been rinsed in water and dried.
Stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Turn shrimp, butter and juices into sauce in double boiler.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat eggs and lemon juice.
Stir in sugar and flour (mixed). Melt butter and stir in.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: mixed winter fruit compote
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine all ingredients except fruit, stirring well to blend.
Stir in the fruit.
Cover tightly with a lid or plastic wrap turned back slightly. Microwave on High for 15 minutes, stirring once after 7 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: orange butter coffee cake
directions: Soften yeast in warm water in mixing bowl.
Stir in 1/4 cup sugar, salt, eggs, sour cream (1/2 cup) and 6 tablespoons butter. Gradually add flour to form a stiff dough; beat well.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double its size (about 2 hours). Combine 3/4 cup sugar, 3/4 cup coconut and orange rind.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole. Top each piece of chicken with
a slice of cheese.
Dilute and prepare soup as directed and pour over chicken and cheese. Sprinkle a small amount of stuffing on top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove top and brown top of chicken, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.
(Exchanges: 3 meats, 2 fats.)

title: creamside pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and Marshmallow Fluff, mixing at medium speed until well-blended.
Add sherbet and mix well again.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cook sugar, butter and dates for 5 minutes.
Take off stove and add pecans, vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Drop (by teaspoon) mixture and roll balls in coconut.
Cool on wax paper.

title: cherry tomatoes in herb marinade
directions: Put tomatoes a few at a time, into a colander and dip into large pan of boiling water for 10 seconds.
Immediately rinse tomatoes with cold water.
Slip off peels and stems and put tomatoes into a bowl.
Stir together vinegar, onion, basil, oregano, salt, pepper and oil until blended, then pour over tomatoes.
Cover and chill for at least 2 hours or as long as 24 hours, stirring gently several times.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut in Crisco.
Mix and add just enough buttermilk to moisten dough so you can drop biscuits with a tablespoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° until light brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Add creamed corn to cornbread mix.
Set aside.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Add picante sauce and simmer 10 minutes. Grease 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 bread mixture in pan.
Add hamburger mixture; sprinkle grated cheese over hamburger.
Top with remaining cornbread dough.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: turkey chili
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, with medium heat, saute onions, crushed red peppers, garlic and oregano in margarine until the onions are tender.
Add the hot peppers and then brown the ground turkey in this mixture.
Add the chili powder and mix thoroughly.
Then add the stewed tomatoes, chopping them with the spatula until they are broken up.
Simmer under low heat for at least 30 minutes.

title: diabetic sweet potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes and mix with other ingredients, except nuts. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Reheat in ovenproof dish at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 servings.

title: apple dumplins
directions: Spray a square Pyrex dish or one large enough to hold apples. Roll out canned biscuit; wrap around apple and place in dish. Boil water, sugar, margarine and sprinkle of cinnamon, if desired. Pour hot water over apples and around in dish.
Bake at 325° until light brown; spoon hot liquid over apples while cooking and press top of biscuit down on apple when dough begins to brown.

title: hot dog sauce 1
directions: Brown beef, garlic and onion.
Stir in all dry ingredients. Add tomatoes, sauce and water; mix thoroughly.
Add salt to taste. Cook over low heat for 3 to 4 hours or when taste seems correct. Pour over hot dogs, hamburgers or anything you wish.

title: vegetable lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Wash and chop spinach. Thinly slice zucchini. Saute vegetables in a little water until soft. In separate bowl, mix Ricotta and egg.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; add tartar and beat until begins to stiffen.
Add sugar, a tablespoon at a time.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: no peek roast
directions: Place meat in oven-proof container with lid.
Pour both soups over meat.
Pour water over soup and meat.
Cover.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Add potatoes and carrots the last 45 minutes.
Don't peek during cooking!
Makes its own gravy.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: macho nacho grande
directions: Brown ground beef and mix in taco seasoning.
Spread bean dip on chips to desired thickness.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Place chips on cookie sheet.
Put 1 teaspoon seasoned ground beef on each chip.
Cover with grated cheese and green chili slices.
Use hotter peppers, if you like.
Heat chips for 3 to 5 minutes.
Top with sour cream and olive slices.
Serve.

title: dutch potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain on paper towel and crumble.
Add onion and celery to bacon fat; cook until onion is soft but not brown. Combine seasonings, wine, vinegar and salad oil.
Add to onion slowly to prevent splattering; heat several minutes.
Mix with potatoes and bacon; toss well.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: barbecued hamburgers
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Cook over low heat 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve on hamburger buns.
This mixture will fill 10 buns allowing 1/4 cup each.
A relish of finely chopped cabbage and onions and pickle relish mixed with mayonnaise is good served on these.

title: wolfpack tailgate barbecue sandwiches
directions: Early in the day, combine vinegar, water, sugar, mustard, pepper, salt, cayenne pepper, lemon, onion and margarine in a Dutch oven.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Remove lemon slices.
Add meat, chili sauce and Worcestershire sauce. Refrigerate.

title: babka
directions: Combine 2 cups of the flour, the yeast, lemon peel and cinnamon.
Heat together milk, sugar, butter and 1/4 teaspoon salt just until warm (115° to 120°), stirring constantly.
Add to dry mixture; add egg yolks.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in raisins and enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth (5 to 8 minutes).
Shape in ball.
Place in greased bowl; turn once. Cover; let rise until double (1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours).
Punch down. Sprinkle almonds in well-greased 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Shape dough in 8-inch ball.
Make hole in center of dough, stretching it to fit over pan center.
Place in pan, fitting tube through hole. Cover; let rise until double (about 1 hour).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 1.

title: chili lover's chili
directions: Cook beef, onion, green pepper and garlic in large saucepan or Dutch oven until meat loses its red color.
Stir in all remaining ingredients except beans.
Cook over low heat, covered, 1 1/2 hours.
Add beans; cook 1/2 hour longer.

title: taco sauce(canning recipe)
directions: Simmer tomatoes, vinegar, salt, sugar, green peppers, onions, banana peppers and garlic for 25 minutes.
Add chili
powder, oregano and parsley; simmer until thick.
Put in jars and seal. Set aside for sealing process to complete.
Eat in 2 months.

title: onion cheese breadsticks
directions: Grease baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Dissolve yeast in warm water in small mixer bowl.
Add flour, parsley flakes, shortening, sugar, salt, garlic powder and egg.
Beat on medium speed 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in onion and cheese.
Pat dough evenly in pan with floured hands.
Let rise in warm place until almost double, about 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 450°.
Cut dough into 3 x 1-inch sticks; brush with butter.
Sprinkle with sesame seed; bake until edges are brown, 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen breadsticks.

title: old time potato dumplings with sauerkraut
directions: Add salt and beaten egg to potatoes and add enough flour to make a thick dough.
Boil 3 quarts of water and 1 tablespoon of salt.
Drop teaspoon size dough in boiling water and cook about 8 minutes.
(If you dip spoon into boiling water, dough should slide off.)
Drain and pour hot butter over all.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add squash and eggs.
Blend well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix well scraping bowl.
Add nuts if desired.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 small pans which have been greased and floured for 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave rice pudding
directions: Bring milk to a boil; add rice and cook until tender.
Add raisins.
Cook a minute or two longer.
While rice is cooking, mix cream, sugar, egg yolks, vanilla and salt together.
Add cream mixture to rice and cook until boiling again but don't cook until it looks like it might be separating; stir every now and then. Remove from microwave and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Chill. It will thicken as it cools.

title: company sandwiches
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Spread mixture on rolls (onion or poppy seed).
On each roll place 2 ham slices, 1 slice Cheddar cheese and 1 slice Swiss cheese.
Wrap in foil and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cook longer if sandwiches are frozen.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in a 13 x 9 pan for 70 minutes at 350°. Cool before frosting.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cake will crack slightly on top.
Cool in pan for 1 hour before removing. For icing, use a cream cheese type or none at all.

title: turkey taco salad
directions: In a skillet, brown turkey.
In a large salad bowl, combine chopped lettuce, diced tomatoes, shredded cheese, brown turkey and crushed corn chips.
Toss lightly.
Add taco sauce and mix.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs with milk.
Grease a deep baking dish.
Add eggs and milk mixture, corn, green pepper and chopped ham.
Season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until center is firm. Serves 4.

title: quick and easy meatless chili
directions: Heat ingredients.
If you care for it a little thicker, remove lid from pan and cook longer.
Serve in bowls and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter 5 minutes.
Put the remaining ingredients, except the bouillon, into a large bowl and toss.
Add the celery and onion.
Pour the bouillon over the top and toss. Stuff into a 12 to 15 pound turkey.

title: creamy turkey and pasta primavera
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, prepare rigatoni noodles according to package directions.
Add broccoli, carrot, green onions and red pepper the last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.
In same saucepan, combine soup, water and cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Add pasta-vegetable mixture and turkey. Over low heat, heat through, stirring often.
Makes 5 servings.

title: flan
directions: Boil anise seed in enough water to cover seed.
Strain and add to other ingredients.
Mix together.
In a 7 to 8-inch glass baking dish, melt 1/2 cup sugar until a pretty caramel color. Pour prepared mixture into baking dish with the caramelized sugar (do not mix!).
Place baking dish into pan of water in oven and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Wash mixed beans and put in large kettle.
Cover with water and place in refrigerator overnight.
In the morning, add 2 quarts water and ham bone.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 2 hours.
Add onion, tomatoes, pepper, lemon juice and garlic.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes more.
Remove meat from bone and return to soup.
Enjoy.
The longer simmered. the better it gets.

title: pastry puffs
directions: Boil water and butter. Add flour; stir rapidly until mixture leaves sides of pan.
Add eggs one at a time, stirring rapidly. Drop on greased cookie sheet 1/2 teaspoon at a time.
Leave sufficient space in between.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 25.
Fill with desired filling.

title: quick tasty beans
directions: Mix all together and cook in skillet or pan on top of stove, stirring frequently.
Can be made with green peppers or onion added, but we like it plain.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef; add onion.
Cook and stir until tender; stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, garlic, oregano and salt. Simmer 30 minutes covered.
Combine cream cheese and milk in separate pan over low heat until smooth.
Prepare noodles as directed.
Layer noodles, meat mixture, cheese mixture, Mozzarella, Parmesan cheeses; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: sesame egg braids
directions: Put warm water in large mixing bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast.
Stir until thoroughly dissolved.
Add milk, sugar, butter, salt and eggs.
Beat in about 4 cups flour.
Then work in enough remaining flour to make dough that is easy to handle.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead for about 5 minutes, or until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Brush top with oil or shortening. Cover with damp cloth; let rise for about 1 1/2 hours, or until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down; cover; let rise again for about 30 minutes, or until almost doubled in bulk.

title: mushroom crab dip
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 3 tablespoons water.
Blend soup, gelatine, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into mold and refrigerate until solid.

title: mexican hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make small and they are much better.
Will feed 7 to 8 people.
We use 2 or 3 peppers to make it hotter.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Make into small balls and brown.
Make gravy from drippings and pour over meatballs in electric roaster or casserole dish. Cook at 300° for 1 1/4 hours. Turn down to 250° for about 1 more hour.
Good over mashed potatoes.

title: quick biscuit
directions: Combine ingredients and place in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° until lightly browned.

title: sandra's orange ball cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well and roll into balls.
Roll balls in crushed nuts or coconut.
Store in cool place or in refrigerator.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Spoon soup and water mixture evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over chicken and soup mixture.
Drizzle melted margarine over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: yakisoba
directions: Slice all vegetables into bite size.

Slowly stir-fry cabbage and carrots in soy sauce and butter in a large wok or frying pan. Fry chicken breasts in butter and garlic salt with a touch of soy sauce until golden brown. When carrots are halfway cooked, add the chicken.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Add the rest of the vegetables.
Boil bouillon cubes. Add Top Ramen noodles.
Put Ramen seasoning packs in vegetables.
Stir vegetables frequently. Drain noodles and place on plate. Top with vegetables and chicken; enjoy.

title: candied pecans
directions: In large bowl, mix egg white and water; in another bowl mix cinnamon, sugar and salt.
Put nuts into egg and water mixture to cover nuts, then put nuts into other bowl.
Stir until nuts are covered with cinnamon mixture.
Butter pizza pan and spread nuts out.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, vanilla and milk together.
Add your choice of filling.
Melt butter in cake pan.
Pour mixture into buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or 1 hour.

title: banana crush
directions: Combine bananas and lemonade concentrate in blender.
Process until smooth.
Combine banana mixture and remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into plastic freezer containers.
Freeze until slushy.
Makes 5 quarts.
Great for parties.

title: polish heaven
directions: Wash Polish sausage.
Cut the ends off.
Slice them down the middle.
Put sauerkraut and grated cheese (just a little) down the middle, then add onions.
Cook in oven at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Serve.

title: chicken over rice
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Pick off bone and chop.
Mix chicken, sour cream and soup together well.
Pour in a casserole dish.
Crumble enough Town House crackers to cover top of dish. Melt a little butter and mix with crackers.
Cover top of chicken mixture.
Cook uncovered in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish (sides and bottom).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water; stir until dissolved, then add reserved juice and water mixture.
Set aside.

title: mantoba slush
directions: Mix
water
and
sugar to boil for 20 minutes, then add remaining ingredients except 7-Up and cherries.
Stir and pour mixture in freezer plastic containers and freeze.

title: pork chops in ginger ale
directions: Saute onions in half the butter until golden brown.
Put in a casserole.
Brown pork chops in remaining butter and place on top of onions.
Scatter brown sugar over them.
Mix tomato puree and flour in bowl.
Add ginger ale and pour over chops.
Season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbee lester's fairy food
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and vinegar in saucepan.
Boil until temperature reaches 310° with a candy thermometer.
Immediately remove from heat and add baking soda fast.
Mix for 10 strokes and pour onto a buttered Teflon 9 x 13-inch pan or cookie sheet.
Don't try to spread; let cool.

title: ho-made ice cream
directions: Mix cornstarch with 1/2 cup milk, add 1 1/2 cups milk and cook in double boiler until thick, beating constantly to avoid lumping. Blend sugar, eggs, salt and evaporated milk in electric mixer.
Add hot cornstarch mixture and beat well.
Add whipping cream, remaining milk and vanilla, pour into electric mixer.
Pack with layers of ice and salt.
Cover freezer tightly and store.

title: cool rise white bread
directions: Rinse a large bowl with warm water before using (water should be warm on wrist).
Sprinkle yeast into 1/2 cup warm water in bowl until dissolved.
Add milk, sugar, salt and margarine.
Stir in 2 cups of flour and beat with rotary beater until smooth (1 minute). Add remaining flour to make a soft dough which leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out on a floured board and knead until smooth and elastic (about 5 to 10 minutes).
Cover with plastic wrap, then a towel and let rest for 20 minutes.
Punch down.
Divide in half. Roll with a rolling pin each portion to an 8 x 12-inch rectangle. Roll longways towards you, sealing in the sides.
Place in 2 greased loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 5/8-inch).
Brush dough with oil.
Cover pans with wax paper for 2 to 24 hours in refrigerator. Let stand 10 minutes at room temperature.
Punch air bubbles.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove and brush with butter.

title: caramel icebox cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll into a roll and chill.
Slice, then bake. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Reserve 4 tablespoons of fat to fry celery and onion.
Then add salt, flour, sugar, vinegar, pepper and water.
Bring this to a boil.
When thickened pour over potatoes and bacon bits and chopped hard-boiled eggs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.
Put in an 8 x 10-inch or 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: shoe peg casserole
directions: Drain corn and peas.
Add remaining ingredients.
Top with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until casserole is set.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Melt margarine and set to cool.
When cool, add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to the mixture.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in sugar and bake on cookie sheet in a preheated 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients all together and drop clumps of dough onto a greased pan. Cook for 8 to 10 minutes. Let cool and serve.

title: fat-free whipped topping
directions: Pour milk into a chilled bowl; beat until foamy.
Add lemon juice; beat until firm.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until stiff. This is a heart healthy recipe.

title: hershey's easy does it #6 chewy chocolate cookie
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts, if desired.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Cookies will be soft.
They will puff during baking, flatten upon cooling.
Cool on cookie sheet until set 1 minute. Remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Blend ingredients in a blender.
Delicious over pasta.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and add applesauce.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add nuts or fruit or both.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fluffy orange pie
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press firmly on bottom and up side of 9-inch pie plate.
Chill. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy; gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then juice concentrate until smooth. Fold in whipped cream.
Pile into crust. Chill 2 hours or until set.

title: apple butter bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually; mix thoroughly.
Add apple butter and chopped nuts.
Mix only until blended.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and
onions together using medium or fine blade of chopper.
Grind
tomatoes
separately.
Pour
enough boiling water over peppers
and
onions to cover.
Let stand 5 minutes, then drain off water.
Bring vinegar, sugar, salt and spices to a boil, then
add tomatoes and peppers.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.
Makes about 12 pints.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage until tender.
Mix all other ingredients together and put in leaves of cabbage. Pour 1 can tomato soup over top.

title: buried treasure pie
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk in bowl until smooth.
Spread evenly in pie crust.
Arrange strawberries on cream cheese mixture.
Prepare whipped topping as directed on package.
Prepare pie filling mix with 1 cup of milk as directed on package for pie.
Fold in one cup of prepared whipped topping. Spoon into pie crust and chill 2 hours.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugars, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes at a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, nuts, oats and peanut butter.
Blend well.
Spoon onto wax paper and cool.

title: plum fun cake
directions: Cream together baby food, oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, soda, salt, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Slowly sift into creamed mixture.
Mix in vanilla and pecans.
Bake in a Bundt pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves good with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: nachos
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine soup and salsa.
Over medium heat, heat through, stirring often.
Arrange tortilla chips evenly on serving platter.
Spoon sauce over chips.
Top with olives, tomato, onions and/or chopped green or sweet red pepper.

title: portuguese style stew
directions: Sprinkle fish with 1/4 teaspoon salt. Cover lightly and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: chocolate tiramisu
directions: In mixing bowl, crumble ladyfingers and add Kahlua and nuts. Mix well.
In separate mixing bowl add Mascarpone and cream and begin to beat.
Add powdered sugar, cocoa, Espresso, and a bit more Kahlua. Beat until stiff peaks are formed.
In individual dessert bowls or champagne flutes, add a layer of crumbs.
Next using a pastry bag fit with a decorative tip, pipe the mixture onto the crumbs and make two repeated layers.
Top with fresh strawberries to garnish.
Serves 6 - 8.

title: ham stuffed peppers
directions: Mix well, stuff into parboiled green peppers.
Place in baking dish with 1/2-inch water.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Heat together the soups and Ro-Tel.
Cut up chicken that has been cooked into bite-size pieces.
Layer as follows in casserole dish:
chicken, slightly crushed Doritos, soup mixture, grated cheese; repeat layers.
Cover casserole dish and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: layered molded salad
directions: Grease a large Bundt pan with Crisco (not oil).
Dissolve strawberry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool and pour in greased pan.
Set in refrigerator before adding next layer.
Dissolve orange jello in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 1/4 cup juice from fruit cocktail.
Cool and add fruit cocktail.
Pour on top of strawberry layer and let set.
Dissolve lime jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Pour on orange layer when it has set.

title: cranberry-banana salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add cranberry sauce and blend well. Chill until it begins to thicken.
Add bananas and pecans.

title: st. louis cake
directions: Mix cake
mix
and
margarine with fork and add 2 eggs; mix again
with
fork.	Spread	in
x
13-inch
greased and floured pan.
Blend
with	mixer,	cream
cheese
and 2 eggs. Gradually add
confectioners	sugar.	Pour over bottom layer. Sprinkle 1/2 to 1 cup chopped pecans and 3 tablespoons confectioners sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper into 2 tablespoons butter. Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, then turn to simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over tossed buns or with crackers.

title: microwave fish fillets with mushrooms
directions: Arrange fish fillets in 12 x 7 x 2-inch microproof baking dish with the thick edges toward the outside of the dish.
Dot with butter.
Stir lemon juice into wine and sprinkle with remaining ingredients over top.
Cover with waxed paper, cook on High (max power) 5 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.
Cooking time:
5 minutes.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: In heavy frypan, heat 2 tablespoons oil over medium-high heat until hot.
Add tortilla strips and cook, stirring, until strips are crisp, 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towel.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon oil to pan.
Add green and red peppers, carrots, onion, garlic and chicken.
Cook until onion is soft and chicken is cooked through, 4 to 6 minutes.
Transfer to 5-quart Dutch oven.
Add tomatoes; reduce heat and cook 5 minutes. Add cumin, corn and chicken broth.
Heat to boiling; reduce to simmer and cook 10 minutes.
Add lime juice.
Divide tortilla strips and cheese among 6 soup bowls.
Ladle hot soup into bowls over cheese.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; add enough salad dressing to hold ingredients together or to suit your own taste.

title: salsa
directions: In large bowl, toss tomatoes, onion and garlic.
Add chopped jalapeno to tomato mixture with parsley.
Toss with vinegar and mix with salt, pepper and cumin.
Chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: devil cake
directions: Combine water, Spry and chocolate squares; melt.
Mix sugar, egg, salt, baking powder, baking soda, milk and flour.
Add chocolate mixture.
Add milk if too thick.
Should be very watery. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Delicious a day after.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush a 3-quart dish with some of the butter.
Mix all together until blended.
Pour into casserole. Cook for 50 to 55 minutes.
(Insert knife to test for doneness.) Cool slightly before serving.

title: mom's japanese barbecued spareribs
directions: Combine all ingredients except spareribs; set aside.
Simmer spareribs about 1/2 hour in boiling water; drain.
Marinate ribs in sauce for at least 1/2 hour; broil or barbecue.

title: chicken mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water, then add 1/2 cup boiling water.
Stir until gelatin is melted.
Let cool and add mayonnaise and rest of the ingredients.
Congeal in loaf pan and serve in slices.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cinnamon raisin biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, raisins, sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Make a hole in center of mixture.
Combine oil and buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just to moisten.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes. Frost with icing when cooled.

title: good stuff
directions: Press ground beef in bottom of baking dish.
Layer carrots, cabbage and potatoes.
Pour soup over top.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes uncovered, then lay cheese on top and bake 5 to 10 minutes more uncovered.

title: pigs in a cornfield
directions: In a casserole, layer white potatoes, sliced onion, cream-style corn and tomato soup.
Cover with pork sausage. Bake, uncovered, in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: In 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes, green pepper and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour soup over mixture.
Cover; bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes.

title: flan(baked custard)
directions: Caramel Custard Syrup:
Before preparing custard, heat 1/2 cup sugar in a 1-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly. Pour mix in cups and let harden, then pour custard mixture.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well and
bake at 375° until top is firm, 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet and sour bean salad
directions: Drain liquid from the 3 cans of beans and put beans in a large bowl.
Chop pepper and onion fine.
Mix chopped vegetables with beans.
In a separate bowl, mix all remaining ingredients.
Pour over bean combination and refrigerate several hours or overnight, until vegetables take on a good sweet and sour flavor.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Melt margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs. Refrigerate crumbs while mixing other ingredients.
Mix topping mix and milk until slightly stiff.
Gradually add pieces of cream cheese and sugar until mixed well.
Refrigerate overnight before adding pie filling on top.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; roll into balls the size of walnuts. Roll in powdered sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These will not or should not be brown.
Bake no more than 8 to 10 minutes.

title: grilled cheesy potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes into approximately 1-inch cubes.
Place in boiling water for approximately 15 minutes.
On two separate pieces of tinfoil, spread out 1/2 stick of margarine.
Drain potatoes; place on tinfoil.
Cover with cheese; seal foil.
Cook on each side for approximately 4 to 5 minutes.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Heat pan; add oil and fry onions until brown.
Add cold rice and saute.
Add eggs, seasoned with soy sauce and salt.
Saute until done.
If you don't like shrimp, add anything like ham, chicken, green pepper or bacon.
Serves 6.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and pour into a container to use last.
Spread pie filling into the pan to cover bottom.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the pie filling.
Pour the melted margarine evenly over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours until bubbly and brown on top.

title: shrimp hors d'oeuvres
directions: Blend all together and chill 1 hour.
(Soften cream cheese first.)
Makes 1 1/2 cups equal 10 people.
Serve on crackers (bland crackers, i.e. Wheat Thins are good).

title: crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together. Chill overnight.

title: orange fluff salad
directions: Sprinkle orange Jello on Cool Whip.
Mix remaining ingredients.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet until flat.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together and spread on crust.

title: farfel kugel
directions: Soak farfel in hot water. Do not squeeze out.
Beat eggs with sugar.
Add to the farfel.
Beat sour cream with cottage cheese and add farfel and egg mixture.
Stir in salt, pineapple and juice and vanilla.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 20 minutes more.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles; drain and rinse with hot water.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Beat eggs with milk, salt, pepper and cheese.
Pour over noodles and bake
1 hour.
This is a good accompaniment to pot roast.

title: quick corn relish(abenaki)
directions: Drain the liquid from corn, reserving 1/2 cup.
Combine corn with onion, pepper and pimento into large bowl.
Combine reserved corn and liquid with vinegar, oil, sugar, dry mustard, salt and pepper in small saucepan.
Bring to boil and pour over vegetables. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomatoes.
Marinate for 8 hours refrigerated.
Add tomatoes just before serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in flour and buttermilk.
Mix food coloring, cocoa, salt and vanilla; stir into flour mixture.
Place in 3 greased layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; cool.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda and salt.
Cream butter.
Gradually beat in sugars and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Blend in vanilla, egg and sour cream (yogurt).
Gradually add flour mixture, beating until smooth.
Stir in chips and nuts (optional). Using rounded tablespoonful, drop onto ungreased (air insulated) baking sheets* 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
After cooling a few minutes, carefully remove from sheets and cool on flat surface.
Makes approximately 2 dozen large cookies.

title: killer cookie bars
directions: Mix brownies as per instructions on box.
Spread into a large greased cookie sheet.
Mix chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, nuts, raisins and coconut in a bowl with the sweetened condensed milk.
Spread mixture over brownies and pat it gently down.
Bake at 325° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and enjoy!

title: baked mussels
directions: Select large fresh mussels with closed shells.
Scrub shells; rinse and remove beards.
Discard any mussels that float.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Throw everything in blender and blend until
smooth.
Place into fondue pot and heat on the stove over low heat until good and warm.
Keep warm over a fondue burner.

title: summer sauerkraut
directions: Combine and heat vinegar, sugar, oil and salt until sugar dissolves.
Pour over sauerkraut.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Serves 6.

title: vegged stuffed peppers
directions: *Allow 2/3 cup cooked rice or 1/2 cup cooked shell beans per pepper half.

title: peanut butter surprise cupcakes
directions: Heat oven.
Line
muffin pan with paper cups.
In large bowl, combine everything, except peanut butter cups.
Fill prepared cups 2/3 full with batter.
Remove wrapping for peanut butter cups and press into batter until tops are level.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well by hand.
Add next four ingredients.
Stir together.
Bake in 9-inch square pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Double for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: leek casserole milanese
directions: Trim and discard leek root ends and any tough outer leaves, several inches from the top.
Clean trimmed leeks thoroughly under cold running water to remove any sand.
Bias-cut cleaned leeks into 1/4-inch slices.
Rinse slices under cold running water to remove any remaining sand.
Drain well and set aside. (You should have about 3 cups sliced leeks).
Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large skillet heat oil over medium heat.
Add leeks.
Cook and stir for 2 to 3 minutes or until just tender.
Remove leeks from skillet; set aside.
In the same skillet cook mushrooms for 3 to 5 minutes or until just tender.
Add wine and bring mixture just to boiling; reduce heat.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes or until most of the liquid has evaporated, stirring occasionally.
Add whipping cream, salt and nutmeg.
Return to boiling.
Cook and stir mushroom mixture for 3 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Add leeks to mushroom mixture.
Pour into lightly greased 1 quart casserole. Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until the topping is golden color and leeks are heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easter basket cake
directions: Cake:
Fix according to directions on box in 2 (8 or 9-inch) round layers.
Cool completely.
Using 1 layer, cut a circle in the center of cake, leaving a ring measuring 1 1/2 inches from the edge to the center.
Remove the center.

title: lenae's cherry cheesecake
directions: Use an
8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix and pat in pan the graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Refrigerate until set and cold.
Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Add whipped cream to taste.
Top with fruit pie filling.
Refrigerate a couple of hours or overnight to set.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix well the first 5 ingredients and add the eggs, oil, carrots, pineapple and pecans. Mix on medium speed until batter is smooth and shiny. Pour batter into 9-inch cake pans that have been greased and lined with wax paper. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cake springs back when pressed in middle with fingers. Cool to warm temperature before icing.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Place all ingredients in a Dutch oven. Cover with water and bring to a slow boil, then reduce heat and simmer over low heat for 2 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and soup together until well blended over medium heat.
Remove from heat; add other ingredients.
Chill 4 hours.
Can be used in a mold.

title: homestyle macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni to desired tenderness.
In a medium saucepan, melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Stir in 4 tablespoons flour until smooth.
Add 2 cups milk and stir on medium heat until sauce thickens.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
In a casserole dish put one layer cooked macaroni, one layer grated Velveeta cheese and another layer of cooked macaroni.
Pour sauce over macaroni.
Top with grated Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: swedish green potatoes
directions: To potatoes, add butter, salt, sugar and sour cream and cream together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat altogether.
Warm at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix together and heat soup, lemon juice and cream cheese with chives.
Pour over broccoli in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.
Serves 6.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: german potatoes
directions: Heat 1 inch salted water until boiling.
Add potatoes.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain and cool.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven 400 degrees and grease a 12 c muffin pan.
Sift Flour, Sugar, Baking Powder and Salt into medium bowl, make a well in center.
Mix Milk, Egg, Oil, Banana and Walnuts into a small bowl.
Pour mixture into well.
Mix batter just until moistened - do not overmix.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups.
Bake until tooth pick inserted in center comes out clean or muffins are golden brown, about 15 minutes.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix flour, yeast, salt and sugar in bowl.
Cut in butter using pastry blender.
Add the egg and then the water.
Mix together until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Knead on floured surface for 5 minutes.
Let rest, covered, for 5 minutes.
Roll out 12 x 17-inches.
Spread with 1 stick of butter.
Sprinkle generously with cinnamon and sugar (lots) raisins and nuts also.
Roll up. Slice 1 inch and place on greased pan.
Squash each slice.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Frost if desired.

title: orange julius
directions: In blender, blend all ingredients and serve.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add frozen strawberries. Stir until thawed.
Set aside.
Break angel food cake into pieces. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour Jell-O and strawberries over cake. Put in refrigerator until set.
Prepare pudding following package directions and spread over Jell-O.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding and sprinkle with walnuts.

title: cheddar baked potato slices
directions: In greased 2-quart baking dish, arrange potatoes in overlapping rows.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix soup, paprika and pepper.
Pour over cheese. Cover and bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight. Great with fresh vegetables.

title: favorite pound cake
directions: Beat oil
and
sugar
to
mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and
beat.	Mix
milk
and	flavoring
together and add alternately with the flour.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour and soda.
Combine other ingredients until fluffy; add egg and vanilla until well blended. Add dry mixture until blended well.
Roll dough into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake 10 minutes until brown.
Cool for at least 1 minute.

title: apple custard torte
directions: Mix flour, oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice apples on top of crust to fill pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Five minutes before done, pour over apples the pudding (prepared according to directions).
Cool and refrigerate overnight.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: nut pudding
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding according to directions and add 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
After the pudding is boiled, add 1 envelope Knox gelatine, soaked in 1/4 cup cold milk.
Mix well, then cool.
When cool, add 1 cup cream that has been whipped and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain all fruits well and cut in small pieces.
Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir fruits into pudding mixture. Add coconut (I use about 1/3 cup).
Add small marshmallows (I use about 3 handfuls).
Mix well and chill before serving.

title: greek tomato and feta salad
directions: Cut tomatoes into bite sized pieces.
Crumble Feta cheese; toss gently with tomatoes.
Add herbs, garlic and pepper.
Serve with Italian dressing on a bed of fresh lettuce.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour; add baking powder and salt.
Combine egg yolks, paprika and corn.
Add flour a little at a time, beating until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Drop from teaspoon into deep fat and fry approximately 2 minutes.
Serve hot with syrup.

title: creamy pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time.
Add flour and unwhipped cream alternately, blending well.
Spoon into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir in milk, sugar, oil, baking powder, salt, egg and 3 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour to make dough easy to handle; turn on well floured board and knead until elastic, 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, greased side up.
Cover and let rise in warm place about 1 1/2 hours until double (if indention remains when touched, dough is ready).

title: low calorie cranberry relish
directions: With chopping blade in food processor bowl, process orange 3 minutes or until orange peel is finely chopped.
Add remaining ingredients and pulse 4 times, scraping sides of bowl between each pulse.
Sprinkle in sugar-free gelatin to taste.
Cover and chill.
Makes 10 servings.
One-fourth cup has 33 calories.
Fat free.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Combine ingredients. Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 15 minutes. Let it cool completely before adding other layers.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Remove stems from leaves.
Soften and blanch leaves by plunging them into boiling water, a few at a time, for a few minutes until they become limp.
Set aside.
Soak and wash rice in hot water.
Drain well.
Mix rice, meat, spices
and melted Crisco.
Place leaves, smooth side down, on a plate or chopping board.
Put about 1 teaspoon of rice mixture in the center near the stem edge.
Fold the stem end up over the filling, then fold both sides to the middle and roll up like a small cigar.
Don't roll too tightly, leave room for the rice to expand during cooking.
Continue until all the filling is used.

title: my cranberry salad
directions: Boil water and stir into Jell-O.
In blender, grind up cranberries with a little water.
Cut up apple, orange and celery. Grind in with cranberries.
Drain off as much juice as you can. With mixer, blend can of cranberry sauce into Jell-O.
Add drained cranberry mixture.
Refrigerate a few hours or overnight before serving.

title: fruit delight
directions: Mix crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press into casserole dish and chill.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and milk.
Spread on crust.
Chill and then spread fruit filling on and chill.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In skillet saute bell pepper, celery and onion in butter; drain.
Add soups and broth; simmer and mix together until heated. Cut up chicken and add to soup mixture.
Cook spaghetti as directed and place into casserole (large).
Add soup mixture and cover with Cheddar cheese.
Place in oven and bake until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Broccoli, cut in bite-size. Top with butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a greased casserole.

title: southern pecan log
directions: In medium-heavy saucepan, combine white sugar, brown sugar, cream and syrup; mix well.
Cook, but do not stir, to 240° on candy thermometer or until small amount dropped in cold water forms a firm ball.
Remove from heat.
Add butter but do not stir. Cool to 150°.
Beat with electric mixer until very thick and light colored.
Stir in 1/2 cup confectioners sugar. Knead in additional sugar until mixture is very stiff.
Divide and roll into four 1 1/2 x 6-inch logs.
Brush with corn syrup.
Roll in nuts.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill; slice.
Store in refrigerator.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup, ground beef, bread crumbs, eggs and onion into 6 patties.
Brown on both sides in skillet until done.
Drain off fat.
Stir in rest of soup and mushrooms on low heat and cook 20 minutes or so, turning occasionally. Serve on fresh hamburger buns or serve with meal with mashed potatoes and gravy over.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar and flour.
Beat thoroughly eggs, milk and vanilla; add butter.
Beat in sugar mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Reduce heat to 350°; continue to bake for 30 minutes.

title: white pound cake
directions: Weigh flour and sift it once, then warm it a little and sift 4 or 5
times with baking powder.
Cream butter; add some of flour and
other	ingredients alternately.
Bake in loaf or layers.
If baked in
loaf,
bake about 2 hours at 300°.
This is an old recipe but very good.
I use an angel food pan.

title: sugar packed pickles
directions: Be sure to use glass or plastic containers.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Start with wafers in bottom of dish, then add layer of pineapple.
Repeat with wafers and pineapple.
Top layer should be wafers.
Mix milk and pudding and cook until pudding begins to thicken. Pour over wafers and pineapple.
Serve hot or cold.

title: mexican dish
directions: Chop tamales and put in bottom of pan, then mix the rest of the ingredients in bowl.
Pour over tamales.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes, then cover with cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted. Serve warm.

title: "gorp" dry mixes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in plastic bags.
Great snack for hiking!

title: charlie's lazy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Toss with all 3 cheeses.
Spoon to cover bottom baking pan.
Mix ketchup, meat and onion with Prego; heat through.
Layer with noodle mixture.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese together.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350°.

title: sassafras tea
directions: Wash sassafras roots well and let dry.
Put six dry roots, 3 to 4-inches in length, in an enamel pot.
Cover with water.
Soak overnight.
Place pot on stove.
Boil roots slowly until a tea, dark in color, is made.
(This will be fairly strong.)
Weaken and sweeten the tea to taste.
(The same roots may be boiled each day for several days, as the flavor increases with each boiling.)

title: firecracker enchilada casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a large skillet until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain.
Add chili powder, cumin and salt; stir well.
Cook meat mixture over low heat for 10 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook thoroughly until mixed over low heat.
Fabulous for grilled chicken, pork chops, ribs, etc.

title: meatballs in secret sauce
directions: Make meatballs from ground beef, brown and drain.
(To stretch the meat you can make meatloaf mixture and form balls, etc.)
Mix chili sauce and grape thoroughly.
Add meatballs.
Cook in oven for 2 hours at 300° or in a crock-pot for 1 hour on high and 3 hours on low.
Serve oven mashed potatoes.
(Don't tell your guests what your sauce is made of until after your meal is over.
The thought of these 2 ingredients together sounds repulsive, but the sauce is very delicious and people will love it if they eat it first and find out your secret later.)

title: stuffed avocados
directions: Slice avocados in half and place on beds of lettuce with a slice of lemon.
Stuff with a mixture of the following: crab meat, onion, pickle relish, mayonnaise, celery, salt and pepper.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into balls. Put the meatballs on a cookie sheet and brown in oven for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: mocha mix
directions: Mix thoroughly and store in airtight container.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Saute onion, add other ingredients (except ham).
Simmer for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Add ham and heat about 5 minutes.

title: belgium meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Make into balls.
Roll in flour, browning in hot oil.
Bake in tomato juice, catsup or tomato sauce for 30 to 45 minutes.
Or may be put in crock-pot for slow cooking.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix together soy sauce, honey and vinegar.
Blend in garlic salt and ginger.
Add oil and onion.
Place meat in shallow dish and pour mixture over.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Turn meat over one time in marinade.

title: saffron buns
directions: Mix Crisco sugar and salt together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Knead these together.
If dough is too sticky, add more flour.
Let stand overnight to rise.
Form into 24 balls or buns in the morning.
Put into a greased pan.
Let rise again about 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over peaches. Chill.
You may add a medium can of drained pear halves if you like.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Put in greased casserole dish, top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple pecan cake
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and eggs.
Add chocolate chips.
Spoon out about one tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: aunt margaret's boiled fruit cake
directions: Boil the first 8 ingredients together for about 3 to 5 minutes. When cold, stir in the egg and baking soda mixture.
Add the flour and bake in a greased bread pan in medium oven at 350° until tests done. This cake is very moist and will keep for a long time.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine soup, water and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted. Add spaghetti, chicken and parsley.
Heat through and serve.

title: peanut brittle("very easy")
directions: Cook in heavy pan to soft ball stage sugar, syrup and water. Add salt and peanuts and cook to hard crack stage.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and butter.
Quickly stir and spread on buttered cookie sheet or platter.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: cajun "dirty" rice
directions: Using a small, sharp knife, remove tough outer skin from gizzards by scraping meat from skin.
Keep blade of knife at an angle against skin as you scrape.
Place gizzards and livers in a food processor fitted with the steel blade; process until pureed.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry onion in skillet until tender.
Add catsup and mustard. Mix well.
Pour into baking dish and bake.
Hot dogs may be added for beanie weenies.

title: miss liza bell's cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add gradually with milk, then flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan or 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: slushy lemonade
directions: In blender container, combine ReaLemon brand and sugar with 1/2 cup water.
Gradually add 4 cups ice cubes, blending until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: water chestnut treats
directions: Soak water chestnuts in soy sauce about 30 minutes or longer. Wrap bacon around water chestnuts and then stick toothpick in it to hold together.
Put in oven or on stove or broil until brown and crispy.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar and cream together.
Add milk and melted butter to the creamed mixture, then the dry ingredients.
Fold the berries in last.
Pour into an 8-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and place on cookie sheet.
Mix Ranch dressing and cream cheese and spread over rolls.
Bake following directions on roll package.
Let cool, then place fresh vegetables and cheese on top.

title: butterhorns
directions: Soften yeast in warm water; scald milk (make sure it's not too hot when you add yeast).
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Add 1 cup flour; beat thoroughly.
Add egg and yeast; beat well.
Add enough flour to make soft dough; knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl; let rise until double.
Divide into 2 portions; let rise 15 minutes.
Roll into circle piece, 1/4 inch thick.
Cut in pie pieces.
Brush with margarine; roll up.
Begin with wide end. Brush with margarine.
Curve into crescent.
Place on lightly greased pan; let double.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Stir in orange juice, orange peel, shortening and egg.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in cranberries.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 55 minutes, then remove from pan and continue cooling.
Freezes well. Makes 1 loaf.

title: peach salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in
2 cups of hot water.
Chill until mixture is slightly thickened.
Drain and reserve liquid from pineapple and peaches.
Drain pears and mandarin oranges.
Fold fruit and marshmallows into gelatin.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: donuts
directions: Heat canola oil in pot until very hot (bubbly).
Open canned biscuits and break each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll each piece into a ball and drop in hot oil.
Remove it quickly and drop into bowl with powdered sugar until covered.
You can fix as many as you want.
We save the oil in an old coffee can and reuse it several times.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Add sugar and salt to beaten eggs.
Add milk slowly and vanilla, beating well.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes.
Then reduce to 200° and bake until light brown.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream shortening, sugar and peanut butter. Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients. Shape into scant teaspoon size balls. Roll each in sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream together.
Spread over chicken in casserole dish; cover with Ritz crackers, melt butter and pour over crackers.
Bake in oven at 350° until crackers are brown.

title: italian chicken
directions: Dice green pepper and onion.
Saute until golden brown in Italian salad dressing.
Add chicken breasts.
Add additional Italian salad dressing, few shakes oregano, garlic powder and pepper.
Cook until done.
Can serve over rice, if desired.

title: potato broccoli puree soup
directions: In soup pot, saute onion and celery in olive oil for 4 minutes.
Add carrots, potatoes, broccoli, seasonings and stock. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cook for 25 minutes. Puree in blender.
Stir in yogurt and reheat.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Add sugar to persimmon pulp.
Add well beaten eggs; stir well. Add soda to milk and stir until foaming ceases.
Add milk to 1st mixture and stir.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Sift into persimmon mixture.
Beat well.
Add vanilla, cinnamon and cream. Put butter into the pan your in and melt.
Pour into batter. Reserve enough to grease pan well.
Beat well and pour into baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cinnamon m&m trash
directions: Mix all ingredients together and mix well.
Store in airtight container.

title: red wine gelatin
directions: In large bowl, stir the gelatin into boiling water until dissolved.
Add the wine and the lemon juice; stir well. Refrigerate until consistency of egg whites, about 2 hours.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Combine egg, milk and Spry.
Add to dry ingredients, beating until smooth. Chill batter to make fritters lighter.
Sprinkle apple slices with lemon juice, spices and sugar.
Dip apples in chilled batter and fry in deep fryer (375°) about 5 minutes or until brown.
Makes 10.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Boil together for 2 minutes the water, candy stick and cloves. Add remaining ingredients. Keep hot and serve.
May be made ahead and reheated.

title: party punch(for adults)
directions: Mix together in large punch bowl and enjoy!

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown ground meat, onions and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and bake in oven 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: avocado dip
directions: Combine in blender until smooth. Add green food coloring if desired.

title: curried rice
directions: Cook 1 cup rice. Saute onion with 2 T. butter. Add rice, onion & curry to soups & water. Mix well. Bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: In large heavy pot, melt butter.
Add onion and celery.
Cook slowly until onion is very soft (about 15 minutes).
Add potatoes, parsley, salt and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until potatoes are tender (about 30 minutes). Stir in milk and heat covered until steaming, not boiling.
Stir in shrimp.
Stir together cornstarch and water and add to soup. Continue cooking and stirring until soup boils and thickens.

title: horseradish and beets
directions: Cook beets in pot of water until beets are done; test with a fork to see if they are tender.
Cool beets and grate fine.
Mix grated beets and horseradish together.
Then add sugar, salt and vinegar.
If you like it a little more sour, add some more salt.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Add sour cream, cheese & salsa. Mix well in crock pot. Cook at least 4 hours on low, or until desired.

title: easy chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in small amount of oleo.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased baking dish.
Grate cheese on top.
Heat in 350° oven until cheese is melted and casserole is heated.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk.
Mix in creamed corn.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: macaroni-chicken salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain, rinse and drain.
Combine with the next 6 ingredients.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard; spoon over salad and toss gently.
Cover and chill.

title: aunt dana's chocolate chip cookies
directions: In small bowl combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside. In large mixing bowl, combine shortening, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Mix in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and salt.
In a bowl, mix all ingredients together except fried onions.
Put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Put on fried onions.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: heavenly chocolate sauce
directions: In double boiler, melt butter and chocolate.
Add sugar a little at a time.
Stir until dissolved.
Add salt, slowly stir in evaporated milk.
Use sauce hot or cold.
Great topping for ice crem and cake!

title: orange punch
directions: Combine Tang, sugar, pineapple juice and water.
Place in freezer until ready to use or until crunchy.
Add 7-Up and sherbet when ready to serve.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Separate eggs, beat egg yolks with shortening and oleo until well blended.
Gradually add sugar and flavorings.
Gently fold in flour.
Alternate with milk.
Add coconut until well blended.
Fold in the egg whites that have been stiffly beaten.
Pour into 10-inch tube or bundt pan.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a food processor, blend rice in coarse pieces. In a large saucepan on medium heat, boil milk and on low heat, reduce the milk to 1/2 the original quantity. Add rice and 2 cups water to milk. Continue cooking on low heat for another 20 to 25 minutes. Add raisins and almonds and cook another 5 minutes. Cool and serve in bowls.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together; rinse them well first.
Let set. Combine sugar, oil, pepper, vinegar, salt and parsley.
Heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and let set several hours.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Parboil 12 peppers in water until tender (not too soft). Brown meat in pot sprayed with no-stick cooking spray.
After meat is cooked and browned, add:
onion, garlic, 2 bell peppers and celery.
Wet French bread (squeeze out water).
Add bread to meat. Season with salt and red pepper.
Add onion tops and parsley.

title: holiday fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in large microsafe bowl on High 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted.
Stir 1/2 way through heating time.
Remove from microwave immediately.
Stir until completely melted.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread into 8-inch square pan.
(A square Corning Ware dish works great!) Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: pecan 'n' honey cookies
directions: In mixer bowl, beat sugar and butter until light. Add eggs, honey and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into beaten mixture, blending well. Stir in oats and chopped pecans.
Chill until firm. Form dough into balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten slightly.
Place a pecan half on each cookie, if desired. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool slightly before removing from pan.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: date and prune pudding
directions: Cut up 2 cubes margarine on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry ice cream in a flash
directions: In a blender container, combine dry milk, sweetener, water, vanilla and 1 cup of strawberries.
Blend just until berries are chopped into small pieces.
Add remaining berries.
Blend until smooth.
Spoon into 2 serving bowls.
Serve immediately.

title: coconut pecan cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Combine all ingredients and roll into balls about size of walnuts.
Bake on cookie sheet until golden brown (approximately 10 to 15 minutes) at 350°.

title: quick and easy dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate until set.
tags: Thank You brand fruit pie filling

title: pineapple ham loaf
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except brown sugar, pineapple and cherries.
Sprinkle brown sugar in pan or baking dish.
Arrange pineapple rings; place a cherry in center of each ring.
Pat ham loaf mixture over entire surface of pineapple.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.
When done, drain off excess liquid in bottom of pan.
Remove cover.
Place meat platter over meat loaf and invert pan.
Makes eight servings.

title: good potato salad
directions: Combine vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed; set aside. Cook and drain potatoes. While potatoes are warm, drizzle with vinegar mixture. Sprinkle with sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt; chill. Add cabbage, corned beef, pickle and onions. Mix dressing (mayonnaise, milk and 1/2 teaspoon salt). Pour over salad and mix lightly. Makes 8 servings.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add juice from the 3 cans of fruit.
Chill until half firm.
Mix in cans of fruit.
Add yogurt.
Set in 1 large oblong glass baking pan until firm.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Ice with Cool Whip.
Garnish top with more grated cheese.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: the max family christmas cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour through eggs with an electric mixer.
Spray three 9-inch round cake pans with Pam.
Pour batter evenly into pans.
Bake for 20 minutes or until done (test with toothpick).
Cool for 10 minutes on rack.
Remove from pans carefully.

title: chow chow
directions: Put the last 4 ingredients in a bag and tie.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices tied in a bag.
Bring to a boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Bring back to a boil.
Remove spice bag.
Pack chow chow in hot jars.
Seal at once.

title: chicken quiche
directions: * We use cholesterol-free egg product.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: cranberry-sauerkraut meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, eggs, onion soup mix, water and crackers.
Form into balls 1 1/2 inches in diameter, then brown in skillet.
To make sauce, combine remaining ingredients in bowl. Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread half of sauce over bottom. Top with meatballs, then remaining sauce.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 to 40 minutes longer.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Makes about 3 dozen, about 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in a serving bowl.
Mix the broccoli, cauliflower and onion with the mayonnaise mixture. Add the bacon bits.
Add the cashews when you're ready to serve.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa. Mix in water, butter and oil. Bring to boil. Add buttermilk, soda and salt. Add eggs. Bake for 20 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken biscuit stew
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 10-inch ovenproof skillet, melt margarine; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly until smooth and bubbly.
Gradually stir in chicken broth and milk; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add chicken, onions, peas and carrots; cook until hot and bubbly. Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Arrange biscuits over hot chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until biscuits are brown.

title: taco salad
directions: In a small bowl, mix sour cream and cream cheese.
In a glass casserole dish, layer meat, cheese, dressing, lettuce, tomatoes and jalapeno peppers, if desired.

title: cooked icing
directions: Cook milk and flour until thick.
Let cool.
Add milk, sugar, Crisco, butter and vanilla.
Beat until well blended and no longer grainy.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, onions and salt for two hours.
Drain, but don't rinse.

title: sauerkraut a la hofbrau
directions: Wash the sauerkraut first with cold water and drain well.
Cook with the other ingredients, simmering for several hours, longer the better.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, slowly melt chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly to avoid scorching.
Remove from heat; beat until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in buttered container.
Chill to firm chocolate.
Cut lightly in squares. Store in refrigerator.

title: mexican chicken(serves 6 to 8 people)
directions: Boil chicken until white. Add 2 1/2 teaspoons salt. Cut chicken in halfway lengthwise and then into thirds widthwise. Spread evenly into baking pan(s).

title: egg substitute
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Makes 1/2 cup or equal to two eggs.

title: spaghetti sauce chicken
directions: In large skillet put cooking oil, chopped onions, celery chopped, bell pepper chopped.
Saute until onions are clear.
Add a little water.
Add chicken (after being deboned).
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Add salt, brown sugar, mustard, ketchup, celery seed and can or 1/2 can of Ro-tel tomatoes depending on how hot you like it. Stir often. Salt and pepper to taste.
When almost done, add can of Cream of Chicken soup.
Add water to keep from sticking. Keep stirring on low heat. (You may substitute Cream of Celery soup and you may substitute other meats for this sauce.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken (save broth).
Debone chicken and chop.
Saute onions and peppers in oil.
Cook noodles in broth.
(Don't drain.) Mix all ingredients.
Bake in casserole (1 large or 2 small) at 325° until bubbly.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix Bisquick and water. Add sausage and cheese. Mix well with hands. Make small balls (can be flattened). Bake for 10 minutes or until browned.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Line bottom and sides of large serving bowl with vanilla wafers.
Slice bananas and arrange on top of wafers.
Pour pudding over wafers around edge of serving bowl.
Top with Cool Whip; decorate top with sprinkles.

title: cauliflower italiano
directions: Cook onion and garlic in salad dressing in skillet until tender.
Add cauliflowerets and 1/4 cup water.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add green pepper; cook until cauliflower is tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook until heated through.
Serves 8.

title: classy carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water to cover, 8 to 10 minutes or until tender; drain.
Place carrots in food processor for 15 seconds.
Add sugar and next 5 ingredients and process until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Pour mixture into 6 lightly greased 8 ounce baking dishes.
Place on a baking sheet and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven, uncover and sprinkle with Pecan Topping.
Bake 20 minutes. Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs together; blend in oil with mixer.
Sift flour, cinnamon, baking powder and soda together.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add pumpkin and blend well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 375° in well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: lamb terrapin
directions: Combine lamb, eggs, olive oil and lemon juice.
Melt butter; add flour and mustard.
Stir stock in slowly.
Add Worcestershire sauce and salt as needed.
Cook and stir the sauce until it is boiling.
Add the lamb and egg mixture.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve it over toast points.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes to tender and dice.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Stir now and again to marinate.
Add potatoes to vegetable mixture and mix.
Serve by itself or put on bed of lettuce.

title: antipasto pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta, drain and rinse with cold water.
In small bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar and seasonings.
In large bowl, combine pasta, dressing and remaining ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate.
Makes 12 servings.

title: baked chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken.
Dip chicken pieces in melted margarine.
Roll in coating mixture.
Place in baking dish; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered. Remove cover; bake another 30 minutes, or until done.

title: vegetable dish
directions: In a large skillet, combine all ingredients except the tomatoes and cheese. Cover loosely and cook about 10 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes and cheese; cook 1 to 2 minutes or until heated through.
Serve immediately.

title: hot cucumber soup(serves 2)
directions: In a saucepan saute green onions in butter until tender.
Add broth and dill weed.
Bring to a boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Add cucumber; simmer 2 to 3 minutes, until tender-crisp.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to box directions.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and place rhubarb in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle dry jello over the rhubarb, then sugar.
Add marshmallows, then spread cake batter over all.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool for a couple of minutes, then turn over.

title: patio chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Serve on lettuce covered plates.
Serves 6.

title: easy cherry pie
directions: Dump cherry pie filling into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over it.
Cut butter over all.
Bake about 20 minutes or until brown.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over Crisco, salt and sugar.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
Add to mixture with beaten egg. Add flour and knead well.
Put in refrigerator until ready to use.
Make rolls out into pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mint wafers
directions: Melt butter with milk in top of double boiler placed over boiling water (upper pan should not touch water).
Add frosting mix; stir until smooth.
Cook and stir over rapidly boiling water for 5 minutes or until smooth and glossy.
Add flavoring and desired food coloring. Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper, swirling tops of candies with teaspoon.
(If mixture thickens, add a few drops of warmed milk.)
Cool candy until firm.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen.

title: western corn casserole
directions: Combine water, green pepper, onion, 1 tablespoon butter and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Cook on high for 3 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil.
Add cornmeal and beat vigorously to eliminate any lumps of cornmeal.
Add corn, cheese, egg yolks and then milk.
Add baking powder and stir to blend.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into cornmeal mixture. Mixture will have tendency to separate into 2 layers.
Place remaining butter in a 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish. Cook on high for 3 seconds or until butter is melted.
Swirl dish to evenly coat bottom of dish.
Pour corn mixture into dish.
Cook at medium-high for about 20 minutes or until center feels fairly firm to touch.
Makes 4 main or 8 side dish servings.

title: cheese and shrimp dinner
directions: Cook green peppers and onions in butter until tender not brown.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes and cook until thickened.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add shrimp and heat.
Combine rice, water and salt; cook as directed.
Serve shrimp mixture with hot rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Cut in margarine.
Add egg, orange peel and orange juice all at once.
Stir.
Fold in raisins and cranberries.
Put into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: creme de menthe punch
directions: Dissolve jello into 1 1/2 cups lemon-lime pop.
Boil; cool. Add thawed lemonade and creme de menthe.
Pour mixture into punch bowl.
Slowly add chilled lemon-lime pop.
Spoon in vanilla ice cream.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend butter and sugar.
Add salt and soda to flour in sifter; sift.
Add eggs and flour mixture alternately to butter/sugar mixture.
Mix well between each addition.
Add sour cream and vanilla; mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube cake pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until done.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: mary's hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs in quarters and put in baking pan or baking dish.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli, using package directions.
Drain well.
Combine with remaining ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Combine ingredients except nuts.
Put on low heat.
Stir until a boil.
Cook until forms a soft ball in cold water.
Beat until fudge is creamy.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: teriyaki flank steak
directions: Marinate flank in remaining ingredients for 2 days, turning twice a day.
Grill on barbecue.
Some marinade can be heated as sauce the first day of cooking.
Do not save marinade for future use after meat has been sitting in it.
Steak should be served cut in thin strips following the grain of the meat.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine egg, orange juice and water; stir in melted butter.
Make a well in the center of dry ingredients.
Add the liquid ingredients all at one time.
Stir only enough to moisten.
Add nuts, cranberries and grated orange rind.
Stir just enough to blend.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 70 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool thoroughly.

title: hot spiced cider
