directions: Combine the cider, sugar and spices in a large saucepan.
Heat slowly to boiling.
Boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve hot garnished with orange slices, lemon slices or rings of unpared red apple with whole cloves forced through peel.
Makes 16 servings.
If desired, chill spiced cider and serve over ice cubes made from apple juice.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and form straws on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°
for 10 minutes.
Remove at once to cooling rack.

title: spinach and cheese squares
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs with the flour until smooth.
Add spinach, cottage cheese, Cheddar, pepper, cayenne and nutmeg; mix well.
Pour into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle the top with wheat germ and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting into squares for serving.
These squares can be made ahead, refrigerated or frozen and reheated at party time.

title: red snapper mexicana
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip fillets in flour, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in skillet and lightly brown fish on both sides, adding more butter as necessary.
Place fish in individual casserole dishes. Top each with salsa, cheeses, chilies, onion and parsley.
Bake about 10 minutes or until done.

title: pickled pigs feet
directions: Mix all together and bring to boiling point.
Scald, scrape and clean feet thoroughly.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and let stand for 4 to 8 hours.
Wash the feet in clean water.
Place them in hot water and cook until tender, but not until meat can be removed from the bone.
Pack feet into clean jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace. Cover with boiling hot spiced vinegar; adjust lids.
Process in pressure canner at 10 pounds for 75 minutes for pints or quarts.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush cookies up in a blender and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice ice cream in layers and place over cookies. Then spread Cool Whip and drizzle chocolate syrup on top.

title: pasta and pepperoni salad
directions: Mix with salad ingredients.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt butter or margarine and remove from heat.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and frost.
Chill in refrigerator for about 20 minutes.
Cut into squares when partially firm.
Refrigerate.

title: paul bunyan sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy. Stir in milk and raisins.
Stir together flour, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir into creamed mixture, blending well.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll chilled dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut with 2 pound coffee can or lid of canister (about 5-inches round).
Sprinkle cookies with sugar on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from pan with spatula. Set temperature at 375°.

title: iced tea
directions: Pour rum, vodka, gin, Triple Sec and orange juice over ice in a tall glass and add enough Coke to fill the glass.
Makes 1 serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Sift flour. Beat eggs and add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Can be prepared ahead; can be frozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Pour in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pat's coffee cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and beat at high speed for 9 minutes. Mix sugar and cinnamon in another bowl.
Grease (heavy) and flour angel cake pan.
Put few nuts in bottom, pour 1/2 batter in and sprinkle with 3/4 of sugar mixture.
Sprinkle with rest of nuts and pour in remaining batter and rest of sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Make thin glaze of powdered sugar, butter and milk to pour over top of cake as soon as you take it out of oven.

title: quick dip
directions: Combine apple jelly and both preserves, dry mustard and horseradish in a bowl and mix well.
Place cream cheese on serving plate or bowl.
Pour sauce on top and serve with crackers.

title: marinara sauce for pasta
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add garlic and saute for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add parsley and onion.
Slowly add tomatoes.
Stir to break up tomatoes.
Add bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer sauce over low heat for about 15 minutes for flavors to blend.
Add some fresh, finely chopped basil leaves, if available.
Serve sauce with spaghetti or other pasta dishes or with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creamy cucumber salad
directions: Peel and chop cucumbers and onion.
Add Miracle Whip just until cucumbers and onion are thinly coated.
Let set in refrigerator until Miracle Whip is creamy consistency (10 to 15 minutes).
Mix and serve.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cheese slices on top of chicken and pour soup and milk over all.
Sprinkle stuffing on top and dot with butter.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: top of the stove rice pudding
directions: Cover rice with 1 quart water.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer over low heat for 20 minutes or until water is evaporated. In a bowl, beat eggs, sugar and salt together.
Add egg mixture to milk.
Then slowly add egg mixture to rice.
Bring all to a boil, then remove from heat.
Add vanilla and raisins.
Pour in large bowl.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pudding will thicken as it cools.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Before assembling casserole, simmer chicken over low flame in large saucepan with water, a small onion, a stalk of celery, salt and pepper for 1 hour.
Cool; skin, bone and slice or break meat into pieces.
Steam frozen or fresh broccoli spears until tender-crisp and drain.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, prepared mustard, curry powder and water chestnuts.

title: hobo dinners
directions: Amounts of ingredients will depend on amount you want to make.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook beans; drain.
Pour beans in casserole dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Cover beans with soup (unheated).
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for approximately 25 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.
Take foil off.
Spread onion rings on top.
Bake for 3 to 5 more minutes, until browned.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine, then add milk, powdered sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Put marshmallows on cake while it is hot.
Pour icing mixture on top of marshmallows and cake.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet cook meat, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in the undrained tomatoes, the water, oat bran, vinegar, brown sugar, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
If necessary, uncover and simmer for 3 to 5 minutes more or until mixture is the desired consistency.
To serve, spoon meat mixture onto toasted hamburger buns.
Makes 5 servings.

title: high-energy muffins
directions: Add All-Bran Buds to the molasses and milk.
Soak for 15 minutes.
Beat the eggs and add it to the bran mixture.
Sift flour and baking soda together and add to the bran mixture.
Add raisins to the bran mixture.
Spray muffin tins with Pam.
Fill tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Calories:
130 per muffin.
Calories from fat:
10 per muffin.
% Calories from fat:

title: easy bread in a jar
directions: You will need 8 wide mouth pint canning jars and lids.

title: cheese sticks(great hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Mix all until smooth.
Chill dough 30 minutes.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick on floured board and cut into 1/4-inch wide by 4-inch long strips.
Twist strips into spirals and bake on ungreased sheet at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: orange cream pie
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cook 2 additional minutes.
Blend a small amount of hot mixture into egg yolk; return all to pan.
Cook 1 minute (do not boil).
Remove from heat.
Add butter, orange peel and juice.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover top with meringue.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix the Veg-All, onions, celery and salad dressing; put in dish.
Crush the Ritz crackers; sprinkle cheese and crackers over mixture.
Melt butter; drizzle over crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put chicken in baking dish.
Mix dressing, soup mix and preserves with small amount of water.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: orange rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, then add 3 cups rhubarb.
Butter pie crust before you add ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: waverly cracker torte
directions: Add 1 c. sugar, slowly.

title: lazy day dinner
directions: You will need a 12 x 15-inch piece of aluminum foil.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all ingredients together and stir well.
Cool overnight.

title: shrimp crabmeat supreme over wild rice
directions: Cook spinach and put into colander to drain well.
Mash to remove any excess water.
Line casserole with spinach, pressing firmly around sides and bottom as if to make an unbaked crust.

title: cut 'n color cookies(quick "paint" kit for colorful treats)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except corn syrup and fool coloring in large mixer bowl.
Mix at lowest speed of mixer until a dough forms, 1 to 2 minutes.
Chill 1 hour, if necessary.
Shape dough into a 12-inch roll; wrap.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: green salad
directions: Drain pineapple; heat pineapple juice.
Dissolve Jell-O in pineapple juice. Cool until it begins to thicken.
Mix with Cool Whip.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Cool.
Nuts can be left out.

title: old south pound cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients; add eggs and flavoring and beat 1 1/2 minutes.
Spoon into heavy Bundt pan which has been greased and floured.
(This is a very thick batter.)
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: baked eggplant with feta cheese
directions: Pre heat oven to 350 degrees.

title: mustard-broiled flounder
directions: Preheat broiler.
Place flounder fillets in a single layer on a lightly greased broiler pan.
Brush fillets lightly with oil.

title: mom's crunchy nut cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine and 2 sugars.
Add the beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add the flour, baking soda and nuts and mix together.
Roll 1 tablespoon of the dough into a ball and place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten each ball with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: rita's pound cake
directions: Sift together 3 times the flour, baking powder and salt.
In separate bowl, cream together until fluffy the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs to creamed mixture and beat thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately in small amounts.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: marinated sweet potato salad
directions: In a large saucepan, cook sweet potatoes in boiling salted water just until tender, about 20 minutes. Cool completely.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine pancake mix, oats, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until dry ingredients are moistened. Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken chalupas(student favorite)
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine until tender.
Add chicken meat, cut in small pieces.
Stir in sour cream.
Sprinkle cheese on top and simmer in covered skillet until cheese is melted. Serve over chalupa tortillas and top with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Set 1/2 cup sugar aside.
Melt margarine in a shallow baking pan in oven.
In a mixing bowl, combine 1 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Simmer fruit with juice in saucepan just until hot.
Take baking pan with margarine out of oven; pour sugar/flour mixture over margarine.
Spoon fruit and juice over batter.
Do not stir. Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over all.
Place baking pan in a larger pan (to catch any drippings).
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes. Delicious with ice cream!

title: face paint
directions: Mix all ingredients together, and store in an airtight container in the refrigerator.
Make several batches using different color of food coloring.

title: cookies 'n cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pans.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except cookies and beat at low speed until moistened, then beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Gently fold in cookies.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 round cake pans. Bake for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans. Cool completely and frost.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Note: Hand chop celery and carrots.
Use scissors for onion tops.

title: joan's carrot cake
directions: Stir ingredients with wooden spoon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
(Test by toothpick inserted comes out clean.
May take less time if glass dish.)

title: basil shrimp and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Heat Crisco oil in large skillet on medium heat.
Add shrimp. Stir-fry about 4 minutes or until shrimp are pink.
Remove to serving dish.
Add all vegetables, except green onions.
Stir-fry until crisp-tender.

title: snow pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together with hand mixer.
Add sugar.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice meat in 1/2-inch strips.
Dredge strips in flour, seasoned with salt, then set aside.
Saute onion and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter for 5 minutes.
Remove vegetables.
Add 2 tablespoons more butter to skillet and add meat strips.
Brown evenly on all sides.
Return onion and mushrooms.
Add garlic and blend in sour cream.
Mix thoroughly and heat through on moderate heat.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water 5 minutes, drain.
Melt oleo in skillet.
Add beaten eggs to broccoli along with onion, cheese, melted oleo and bread mix.
Beat well.
Pour into pan or skillet. Bake at 350° until golden.

title: creamy noodles and peas
directions: Mix margarine, undiluted cream of chicken soup, celery seed, water and cooked green peas in saucepan, stirring constantly, until completely mixed. Pour into pot of drained egg noodles and mix well.

title: sara's chicken casserole
directions: *May substitute 1 whole fryer.

title: jane's favorite taco salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, mix lettuce, onion, tomatoes, cheese and beans together; toss well and refrigerate.
Just before serving, add browned meat, chips and Catalina dressing; toss lightly and serve immediately.

title: meat loaf soupreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Mix well.
In large, shallow baking dish, shape into a loaf. Bake 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: honey mustard chicken(cooking time:  15 minutes)
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook chicken for 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, milk, honey and mustard.
Top each chicken piece with orange slices.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer for 5 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of chicken soup

title: poor man's chop suey
directions: Cook hamburger in large 6-quart pot until browned; drain.
Add ingredients in layers as listed.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
When done, thicken with 2 tablespoons cornstarch and 1 tablespoon water.
Serve over steamed rice or chow mein noodles (hard).

title: apple crisp
directions: Pare and slice 6 apples and put in a greased baking dish. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Mix together flour, sugar, pinch of salt and 1 1/2 teaspoons baking powder.
Work as for pie crust. Add butter or margarine and one beaten egg.
Sprinkle over apples and bake in hot oven until apples are done.
Serve hot with milk or with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: super duper cookies
directions: Melt butter with chocolate; cool.
Add sugar and vanilla and blend thoroughly.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and nuts and mix thoroughly.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Form into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in powdered sugar and bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, oil, water and eggs. Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/4 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill several hours.

title: four layer pie
directions: Mix together and press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Let cool.

title: mock pierogi dish
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Cook potatoes until done; drain and put 2 packages cream cheese in right away. Start mixing and add more cream cheese as needed.
Melt butter and put in sliced onions; brown until tender.
In large 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, put onions and butter on bottom of dish, then noodles, cheese and potato mixture and keep alternating layers. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holy smoke
directions: Combine butter, flour and pecans.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients.
Add crushed nacho chips and sprinkle with Catalina dressing.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine graham crackers, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/3 cup melted butter.
Press firmly in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill at least 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese with 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding (any flavor) as directed, using 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Spread 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip over pudding.
Garnish with graham cracker crumbs.

title: don's favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, saving 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Pack neatly in meat loaf pan.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top of meat loaf.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve both packages of Jell-O in boiling water.
Add rest of the ingredients and chill.

title: doritos taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and cayenne pepper together. Spread on a plate and chill for 1 hour.
After chilled, spread on taco sauce.
Sprinkle on onions and peppers.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Serve with Doritos chips or crackers.

title: apricot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix until well blended.
Pour into a well-greased and floured pan (10-inch tube or Bundt pan).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Yields one 10-inch cake.

title: potatoes chantilly
directions: Combine mashed potatoes, butter, salt and pepper in mixing bowl; beat until fluffy.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart deep casserole dish.
Spread whipping cream over the top; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and top is browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: In bowl, mix flour, butter and nuts. Press into 9 x 12 pan. Bake 20 minutes in 375° oven. Cool.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and canned milk in a boiler and bring it to lukewarm long enough to melt sugar.
Mash bananas and add to mixture after taken off the heat.
Add vanilla and dash of salt. Put mixture in ice cream freezer and fill freezer with milk.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed of electric mixer for 5 minutes. Gradually beat in sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread in a greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients together well for 15 minutes. Remove spices and add sugar.
Dissolve.
Add tea in cheesecloth bag.
Dip up and down until color you want.
Lastly, add juice of oranges and lemons.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine cereal and water; let stand until water is absorbed. Blend eggs, sugar, syrup, butter, vanilla and salt.
Fold in softened cereal.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until filling is puffed completely across top.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs together thoroughly. Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Combine with shortening mixture.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon (fun part!).
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
These cookie puff up at first, then flatten out with crinkled tops.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Cut oil into dry mixture until consistency of corn meal.
Beat 1 egg well. Add vinegar and ice water.
Stir this mixture into dry ingredients.
Makes 3 large shells.
Dough can be frozen.

title: egg foo young
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a well greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.
Slice and serve with extra soy sauce.

title: mom's bread
directions: Dissolve and raise yeast in 3/4 cup water (follow directions on package).
Heat canned milk just until bubbles (be careful not to burn).
Pour sugar into the hot milk and dissolve.
Then add stick of margarine to the milk and sugar mixture and melt and dissolve. In large bowl, mix 3 cups flour and the salt.
Add the beaten eggs and mix well with wooden spoon.

Add 3 more cups flour and 1/2 of the milk-sugar-margarine mixture and mix well with wooden spoon. Add 2 more cups flour and the other half of the milk-sugar-margarine mixture and mix with wooden spoon.
(Mixture will be difficult to mix fully, just mix as best you can.)
Add remaining cup of flour and the raised yeast mixture and knead well with hands until mixture forms a soft ball.
The dough will pull away from sides of bowl completely.
There should be no dough left on bowl when you are done kneading.
You may need to add more flour if the dough remains too sticky.
Do not add more than 10 cups of flour!
Knead about 10 minutes after soft ball is formed.
Raise dough in bowl sealed with lid in warm place for 2 to 6 hours.
It is done when dough reaches top of bowl and pops lid and raises 1 to 2 inches over rim (about 3 times its original size).
Next, place dough on floured-covered board and squeeze out air.

Divide into 7 small loaf size (7 3/8 x 3 5/8 by 2 1/4-inches) or 4 regular size (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 5/8-inches) or 4 regular round size bread pans. Place dough in greased loaf pans and raise again in warm place covered with cloth (oven) for 2 to 4 hours until pans are about 1/2 inch above pans.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Bread is done when toothpick comes out clean.
Cool about 15 to 20 minutes before removing from pans.

title: raspberry lemonade mold
directions: Drain raspberries and reserve the syrup.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in softened ice cream.
Add reserved raspberry syrup and lemonade concentrate, blending until smooth. Chill until partially set.
Fold in raspberries and pecans.
Pour into 6-cup ring mold or another attractive mold.
Chill overnight until set.
After molding, fill the center of the ring with fresh blueberries or grapes.
Serves 8.

title: baked stuffed shrimp #1
directions: Amounts of all ingredients depend on the number of shrimp used.

title: coconut balls
directions: Melt chocolate chips and 1/2 stick paraffin wax on low heat. Mix ingredients and shape into balls.
Drop balls into chocolate mixture onto wax paper and let cool.

title: sesame broccoli
directions: In frying pan, add 1 tablespoon sesame oil.
When hot, add cut-up broccoli; cook 1 to 2 minutes, then add sesame seed and cook for 1 minute.
Add more oil, if needed, then add water and sugar mix.
Cover and steam 1 minute.
Serve.

title: sausage royale
directions: Fry sausage rounds, over low heat until slightly browned. Drain sausage on paper towel.
Pour off fat except 3 tablespoons. Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in same pan until wilted, not brown.
Add 2 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boil and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add sausage and raw rice.
Pour all into a greased casserole with tight fitting lid.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: southern mexican corn bread
directions: Brown seasoned chuck.
Drain and set aside.
Combine all other ingredients.
Spoon 1/2 batter into 2-quart casserole that's been sprayed with vegetable spray, then pour browned chuck in topping with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: quick brownies
directions: Melt margarine and stir in cocoa.
Add sugar and salt.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix and bake in an 8-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Glaze with icing.

title: italian wedding cookies or "jeannettes"
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour together.
Add flour to make a soft dough.
Roll and cut into long strips.
Wrap each strip around finger and drop on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Dip the tops in icing or put in large
bowl and coat the entire cookie.
Makes 80 cookies.

title: instant pistachio-coconut mousse mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Keep in an airtight container or resealable plastic bag.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and onion until done.
Then boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Break chicken into small pieces (strips).
Drain spaghetti.
Add chicken, peas, mushroom soup, tomatoes and cheese to spaghetti.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine all and beat with electric mixer until well blended. Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate.
You can put this in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan and cut into squares rather than a pie pan.

title: goulash
directions: Drain peas, reserving liquid for cocktails or soup.
Mix together peas, peanuts, celery, rice and salt in bowl.
Melt butter or margarine in small saucepan; add flour.
Stir well until blended, then add milk gradually and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Pour into rice mixture and mix thoroughly. Turn into greased medium-sized baking dish; press firmly with spoon.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before unmolding on platter.
Serve hot or cold with chili sauce or meat relish.
If served cold, loaf may be garnished with sliced, hard-cooked egg and watercress salad.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: yummies
directions: Cream oil and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in oatmeal.
Add coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: shipwreck
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, salt and celery.
Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Place alternate layers.
Pour soup over top; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Economical and delicious.

title: pepper roast
directions: Slice garlic and tuck into several places on roast; sprinkle with salt.
Rub oil on roast.
Coat top of roast with cracked pepper.
Place in pot and insert meat thermometer.
Put roast in cold oven.
Set temperature to 450° for a rare roast (120°).
Check meat thermometer after 30 to 40 minutes; for medium roast (130°) check meat thermometer after 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese and rosemary pinwheels
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into four rectangles (per can).
Press seams to seal.
Crush rosemary slightly to release more flavor.
Combine cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, and rosemary and mix until well blended and creamy.
Spread cream cheese mixture on each rectangle.
Starting on the short side, roll up each rectangle and pinch edges to seal.
Cut each roll cross-wise into six slices.
Place slices on baking sheet, cut side up, and bake 12-15 minutes or until golden brown.
Best if served warm.
Makes 48 bite-sized pinwheels.

title: baked fish with mushrooms
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Arrange fish in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 5-inch baking dish, turning under thin edges.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cook mushrooms, onion and tarragon in margarine until tender.
Spoon over fish.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: cornbread dressing(with sausage and dried fruit)
directions: Crumble the sausage into a 10- to 12-inch frying pan over medium-high heat. Stir often until sausage is lightly browned, about 5 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer sausage to a large bowl.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft, but not brown.
Combine eggs, cream, salt, nutmeg, cayenne and pepper.
Beat with rotary beater until well mixed.
Sprinkle pie shell with crumbled bacon; cover with cheese.
Pour in egg mixture carefully.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package. Saute broccoli and sliced mushrooms in 1/2 cup butter, garlic, Parmesan cheese and oregano. Fry until most of the butter is absorbed. Cook noodles and mix together.
Add 1 cup melted butter to half and half, Velveeta (cut up) and small can of tomato sauce.
Cook until sauce is smooth. Mix with broccoli and noodles.
Best if sits awhile.

title: chicken pie
directions: Layer greased dish with chicken and eggs.
Sprinkle with flour.
Melt and cool the oleo and milk.
Pour over all and bake in a 400° oven until bubbly and brown.
(English peas may be added if desired.)

title: bleu cheese dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all the ingredients and mix well. Chill to blend flavors.
Place in resealable plastic bowls.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine corn, sugar, salt and pepper; add eggs.
Add milk to butter.
Heat until butter is melted.
Add to corn and eggs. Pour in baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together the eggs, sugar, carrots and pineapple.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 10 x 14-inch pan (greased and floured).

title: italian beef
directions: Cut tiny slots in roast.
Put one thinly sliced garlic piece in each slot.
Pour pepperoncinis, juice and all, over roast. Sprinkle Italian seasoning, salt and pepper over entire roast. Bake in 300° oven for 4 hours or use crock-pot.

title: stir-fry pepper steak
directions: Cut sirloin into bite size pieces; set aside.
Cook garlic in wok for 15 seconds, then add cut vegetables.
Add a little oil if necessary.
Cook until done; set aside.
Add meat and cook until done.
Mix soy sauce, pepper, cornstarch and Worcestershire sauce. Pour into wok with meat.
Cook for 2 minutes, then add vegetables and cook for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: mom's applesauce cake
directions: Mix together sugar, spices, flour, salt and raisins.
I heat applesauce in microwave, add margarine until melted.
Then put in soda and add applesauce mixture to the rest.
Bake in 11 x 7-inch pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Spoon flour into dry measuring cup.
Level off and pour flour into bowl.
Add baking powder and salt into flour and mix.
Cut in shortening with fork resembling coarse meal.
Add milk, stir with fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot broth and cook.

title: white icing
directions: Melt marshmallows and Karo syrup over low heat.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then add sugar and beat.
Add vanilla, beat. Pour hot syrup over whites, while beating.
Do not return to heat. Frost cake when mixture is right consistency.

title: baked chicken-n-potatoes
directions: Wash chicken; put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut up in wedges and wash potatoes, with or without peel.
Put in pan.
Sprinkle spices over top.
Add oil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: spice plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni dish
directions: Cook
macaroni,
as directed on box, until almost done; drain. Return
to
stove,
in large pot, and add tomatoes and cheese cubes, stirring constantly over low heat to melt cheese and tomatoes.
Leftover
meat
can
be	added
or topped with Velveeta cheese and melted.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Beat egg, flour, salt and mustard until smooth in a 1 cup container.
Fill cup with milk.
Boil 1 cup sugar and 1 cup vinegar.
Pour in egg mixture and stir until it thickens.
Cool before adding to potatoes or macaroni.
Makes a large amount.

title: black midnight cake
directions: Sift flour first; then measure and sift all dry ingredients. Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs.
Alternately add liquid and dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until done.
Makes two 8-inch round layers.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients.
Cook and drain elbow macaroni.
Add elbow macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and chill.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together except for bacon. Lay bacon on top. Bake 325° without cover for 2 hours.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Lay boned chicken breasts in shallow pan.
Place a slice of Swiss cheese on each chicken breast.
Pour cream of chicken soup with 1/4 cup water over chicken.
Sprinkle Pepperidge Farm stuffing on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together the sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add apples. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in moderate oven about 30 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan or this can be made into cupcakes.

title: creamy chocolate sauce
directions: Heat milk and chocolate on low.
When chocolate is melted, beat until smooth.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir into milk and chocolate and cook 5 minutes, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla and serve hot or cold.
Real good over ice cream or cake.

title: chicken curry
directions: Cut finely sliced onion.
Heat oil at medium flame in a skillet.
Add onion to it; stir it occasionally, until onion is golden brown.
Remove onion; set it aside.
Put chicken in the skillet.
Add black and white cumin seed, cinnamon, cardamon, cloves and black pepper; stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add garlic, ginger, turmeric, coriander powder, salt and paprika; let it cook. Keep stirring.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix until crumbly the flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, margarine and cinnamon.
Press 1/2 mixture into a greased pan.
Cover this mixture with the diced rhubarb.
Combine sugar, water, cornstarch and vanilla; cook until thick and clear.
Pour over the rhubarb. Top with the remaining crumbs; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: *steak and onion pie
directions: Cook onion slowly in shortening until yellow.
Remove onion. Roll meat in mixture of flour, seasonings and spices.
Brown in hot fat.
Add boiling water; simmer, covered, until meat is tender, about 1 hour.
Add potatoes and cook for 10 minutes longer.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Mix all but sausage; bring to boil.
Cut sausage into bite size pieces and add to mixture.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sparkling fresh salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Cool slightly.
Add ginger ale.
Arrange apple slices, red side down, in large flutes in bottom of Bundt pan.
Alternate with grapefruit sections in creases.
Add a little of the gelatin and chill quickly in the freezer until set.
Add the chopped apple, pineapple and remaining grapefruit to gelatin and pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop from spoon on to cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 - 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Mix juice, sugar, flour and 1/3 of the cheese to make a sauce.
In 1 quart buttered baking dish, layer pineapple, 1/3 of cheese, and the sauce.
Stir crumbs with melted butter.
Spread over casserole.
Top with remaining 1/3 cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Cut wings in half (discard end section).
Place in container and pour marinade (remaining ingredients) over them.
Refrigerate overnight, turning ever so often.
Put wings on a cookie sheet and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Do no reuse marinade.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into buttered casserole. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients, except broccoli.
Add broccoli that has been fully drained.
Pour into an ovenproof casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Gently toss all ingredients together.
Arrange in shallow pan or dish.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Cut into squares and serve on "lettuced" plates.

title: chocolate brownie bundt cake
directions: Mix together .
Spread in a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: tennessee cornbread
directions: Mix well. Bake at 350° until firm and brown.

title: karo oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Stir in egg whites and corn syrup (lemon or vanilla) until well mixed.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until firm.
Do not overbake. Remove.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: company potatoes
directions: Dice potatoes into shallow baking dish.
Combine sour cream, cottage cheese, softened cream cheese, chives and Cheddar.
Mix into potatoes.
(This can be done up to a day ahead.)
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
This is my most requested recipe.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan.
For cake, combine cake mix, egg whites, water, oil and poppy seed in large bowl.
Prepare, bake and cool cake following package directions for no cholesterol recipe.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Blend in chocolate.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost with chocolate frosting.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Melt margarine and add to crushed graham crackers.
Mix well and pat into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 5 minutes.
Cool. Place single layer of strawberries in cooled crust.
Sprinkle with sugar substitute.
Cook boiling water and cornstarch until clear. Add gelatin.
Cool.
Pour over strawberries in crust.
Chill pie. Spread whipped topping over pie when set and chilled.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fry in skillet like pancakes.

title: crock-pot patties
directions: Mix all but last ingredient together and form into patties. Roll in flour and brown in oil. Place in crock-pot in layers. Cover each layer with soup. Cook 4 hours on high.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° or slower temperature.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in saucepan, stirring frequently. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: french vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, salt, vanilla, Eagle Brand cream and half and half.
Pour into ice cream can.
Finish filling with whole milk.
Freeze according to freezer directions.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
In large bowl, combine the 11 ingredients.
Blend well.
Add macaroni and toss lightly until well combined.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir. Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: tuna and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Drain and rinse with hot water.

title: italian meat sauce
directions: In Dutch oven, combine onion, meat and garlic; cook until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Skim off excess fat; add remaining ingredients and 2 cups water.
Simmer, uncovered, 3 hours or until sauce is thick; stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over hot spaghetti.
Pass the Parmesan cheese.

title: unbaked peanut butter cookies
directions: Boil for 1 minute the cocoa, sugar, shortening and milk. Remove from heat and add the peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla. Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Let cool for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, 1 cup strawberries and flour gently until slightly thickened.
Place remaining strawberries in pie shell.
Pour cooked mixture over top.
Cool.
Serve with cream.
Serves 6.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Combine the cabbage, bell pepper, and onion.
Rinse and drain.
Pour the oil into a large skillet and add cabbage mixture. Stir to mix.
Cover.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is wilted and peppers/onions are tender.
Sprinkle soy sauce over top and mix.
Taste and add Cavender's (or you can use salt & black pepper). Stir in butter. 4 to 6 servings.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix all ingredients.

title: variations of seasoned popcorn
directions: Asian flavor:
mix 2 t low-sodium soy sauce, 1/2 t garlic powder, 1/8 t onion powder and 1/4 t ginger.

title: orange butter toast
directions: Cream the butter until light and fluffy, then gradually add the
sugar.
Blend	in
the
grated orange peel and orange juice. This will spread about 8 slices of toast.

title: mom's french dressing
directions: Mix all together by beating or shaking in container.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: "beans and greens" salad(10 servings)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except lettuce.
Toss very gently.
Line large bowl with lettuce; fill center with bean-vegetable mixture.

title: lemon-pecan sticky rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, combine sugars, margarine, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Reserving 1/4 cup, pour remaining lemon mixture into 9-inch round cake pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Separate rolls into 8 rectangles.
Spread with reserved 1/4 cup lemon mixture.
Roll up jelly roll fashion, beginning with short sides; seal edges.
Cut in half.
Place rolls, cut side down, in prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until browned.
Loosen sides.
Immediately turn onto serving plate.
Do not remove pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove pan.
Serve warm.

title: potato and egg dish(usa)
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Fry over medium heat in bacon drippings until tender.
Beat eggs and pour over potatoes.
Cook until eggs set.
Serve hot.
Serves 2.
For each extra person, add 2 potatoes and one egg.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl cream shortening and sugar. Add bananas, eggs and extract. Mix in dry ingredients, one at a time, and add alternately with milk.
Add nuts or raisins. Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Fry ham, onion and green pepper in small amount of bacon grease.
Add rice and black-eyed peas.
Heat through and add salt and pepper.

title: shrimp stroganoff
directions: Saute shrimp in 6 tablespoons margarine.
Remove shrimp and reserve.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons margarine, mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add flour.
Stir in consomme, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce, dill and salt.
Simmer 2 minutes. Add sour cream.
Add shrimp.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve over rice and noodles.
Serves 8.

title: orange julius
directions: Put in blender and blend about 25 to 30 seconds.

title: the black-eyed pea's baked squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut off tips of squash and cut each squash into 3 to 4 pieces.
Cook in a small amount of water until tender; drain and mash.

title: chicken sauce
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in sherry.
Sauce is now ready for use.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil and debone chicken. Cut tortillas into 1/4 inch strips. Line bottom of 13 X 9 inch pan with tortillas. Place chicken on top of tortillas. Mix soup, milk and tomatoes. Pour over chicken. Put shredded cheddar cheese over top. Cook at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes.

title: diet soup
directions: Cut vegetables in bite sized pieces.
Mix all in one large pot.
Cook until tender.
No seasons needed.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together dry ingredients with 1 1/4 cups sugar.
Blend in oil, orange juice and eggs.
Do not mix more than 30 strokes.
Mix blueberries with 1/4 cup sugar.
Fold in blueberries.
Put into slightly greased muffin tins.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: angie's chocolate bundt cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix first 6 ingredients.
Pour 1/2 batter in pan.
Sprinkle bits and nuts over top.
Add rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Put chicken in a big pot.
Cover 3/4 with water.
Cook chicken until it comes off the bone; remove to cool.
Cut carrots and celery; chop onion.
Add to broth.
Add 4 cups of water and bouillon cubes.
Cut up chicken from bone and add.
Cook until tender.
Cook pasta or rice and add to soup.

title: heavenly cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients for filling, except spice.
Cook in a double boiler until thick.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg or cinnamon on the top.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Pack firmly in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty into shallow baking dish or pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: skillet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cocoa into 10-inch greased skillet.
Add nuts.
Mix vanilla, vinegar, cold water and melted butter together and add this to ingredients already in skillet.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread on topping and put in broiler (low heat) for 3 to 5 minutes until coconut is toasted.

title: whipped milk punch
directions: Use blender if possible.
Put in all ingredients and blend until smooth.
Otherwise use electric mixer to whip until smooth. Garnish each glass with ground nutmeg.
Serves 6.

title: arroz con grandules(rice and beans)
directions: Chop onion, garlic and green pepper into fine pieces in a large frying pan.
Saute all ingredients with tomato and peas until onion is transparent.
Add tomato sauce and saute, stirring mixture.
Add water and rice.
Cook on low heat until water evaporates.
Serve topped with pimento.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: soft nachos or mexican quiche
directions: Layer in pan the Cheddar cheese, chilies and Monterey Jack cheese.
Mix eggs and half and half together and pour over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before cutting.

title: easy top cake
directions: Bake cake according to the directions on the box.
When cake is still hot, pour the Eagle Brand milk on top of cake.
Poke with toothpicks so milk will seep through cake.
Layer caramel topping next.
Crumble up candy bars and drop on top of cake.

title: jaime's salad
directions: Mix all ingredients into a big bowl.
Put any kind of dressing on it.

title: layered mint chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with 1 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Add vanilla.
Spread 1/2 mixture into wax paper-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill 10 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Set
oven
temperature	at
Melt

and cocoa. Remove from heat; stir in sugar and eggs and mix well. Add flour,
