Mix well.
Spoon batter into a greased
x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes. Sprinkle marshmallows on warm cake and cover with frosting.

title: special waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Combine eggs, creamer and oil. Add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Cook as per waffle maker directions.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes(with curried rice)
directions: Wash and dry the cherry tomatoes.
Using a sharp paring knife, remove a small portion of the stem end of each tomato and scoop out the tomato pulp and seeds.
Turn upside down onto paper towels to drain.
Combine the rice, bell pepper, onion, celery, relish, and garlic in a large bowl.
Mix well.
In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, nutmeg, curry, and cloves.
Mix to blend. Add mayonnaise mixture to the rice mixture and mix well.
Taste and add salt and black pepper, if needed.
Stuff the tomatoes, cover with plastic wrap, and refrigerate until time to serve.

title: tom and jerry mix
directions: Mix the water, rum and brandy in a mug.
Put 2 tablespoons of the Tom and Jerry mix on top and sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook thawed spinach on medium heat 5 minutes; drain.
Mix spinach and remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook and drain rotini noodles. Add taco seasoning mix to browned and drained ground beef; mix well. Add all other ingredients. Serve over shredded lettuce with sour cream, shredded cheese and taco chips on the side.

title: macaroni and broccoli salad
directions: Cook shells; drain. Mix dressing with shells. Add all other ingredients, except tomatoes. Let set overnight in refrigerator. Add tomatoes before serving.

title: broccoli or spinach casserole
directions: In large skillet, saute hamburger, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Place spinach or broccoli on top of mixture.
Let it steam until mixable.
Add soup, sour cream and rice.
Mix well and put in casserole dish.
Top with Jack or Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: company chicken
directions: Spread chicken with sour cream and roll in crumbs.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Lay chicken one piece at a time and turn butter side up.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Bake chicken 45 minutes at 350° or until tender. Saute onion in butter until tender; add remaining ingredients altogether and simmer 1/2 hour.
Drain grease from chicken and add barbecue sauce.
Bake another 30 minutes, covered.

title: crammin' grilled ham and cheese
directions: Upon arrival home from school, turn on favorite T.V. show. Melt one tablespoon butter in frying pan.
When butter sizzles, add two slices of bread (lightly buttered on one side) with buttered side down.
Then place one slice cheese and one slice ham on each piece (cheese first).
Allow for each piece of bread to slightly brown.
Flip one half onto the other and continue to brown, flipping occasionally, until cheese has melted.
When bread is toasted (but not burnt), remove and place on plate next to favorite side dish.
Cut diagonally for best flavor!
The rest is simple. Relax and enjoy your favorite show and begin crammin'!
Better make at least two to be safe.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Add package of onion soup mix.
Blend in onion, pepper and corned beef.
Let set 12 hours. (The longer it sets the better the flavor.)

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Arrange 6 slices of bread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with cheese, ham, chillies and remaining bread.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over bread and refrigerate for 1 hour or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until custard is set in center.
Serves 15.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream together the Crisco, butter and sugar in a large mixer bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Blend dry mix into creamed mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes (do not overbake).
Cookies will be soft and puffy during baking and will flatten while cooling.
Cool on cookie sheet resting on wire rack until set for a minute.
Remove to wire rack to completely cool.

title: dogs in a blanket
directions: You will need 10 toothpicks.

title: debbie's eggs newport
directions: With a few drops of lemon juice, mix first 3 ingredients together well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir in gently, reserving some bacon to garnish the top.
Bake uncovered at 350° about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve on toasted English muffins.
May be prepared a day or so ahead, covered and refrigerated.
Serve with sliced tomatoes, orange juice and coffee!!!

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Empty the pie filling into pan. Add the pineapple.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the pineapple. Cut the butter or margarine into slices and place on top of cake mix. Add the nuts.
Bake 40 minutes to 1 hour at 350° until light brown. Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: cheese garlic biscuits(similar to red lobster's)
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix margarine and garlic and brush over hot biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients together in large bowl.
Grease muffin tin and fill half full.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients well and take 1 cup for topping. Make a well and add remaining ingredients. Mix together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in casserole dish.
Place desired amount of pork chops on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: orange pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco with sugar, then add eggs and blend. Add the other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in tube cake pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: oil pie crust
directions: Blend together with pastry blender.
Roll out between wax paper.
Makes 2 crust pie.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix wafers, walnuts, powdered sugar and cocoa.
Stir in rum and corn syrup. Roll in small balls.
Roll into powdered sugar or chocolate shots.
Refrigerate in tightly covered container for several days before serving.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Boil all ingredients together.
Add 1/4 teaspoon vanilla. Remove from heat and add 1 1/2 cups pecan halves.
Toss quickly; turn onto waxed paper and separate until cool.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine onion and vinegar and let set for a while.
Add mayonnaise, salt, pepper and paprika; mix.
Mix pasta and other ingredients with sauce and toss.
Chill for several hours. Garnish with parsley.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Mix with pepper and onions.
Mix all other remaining ingredients together, then combine with cabbage.
Add dressing to slaw.
Mix thoroughly.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Slice tomatoes and heat slowly in a saucepan with lemon (sliced thin), sugar, salt, butter and spice.
Cook until tomatoes are tender.
Add cornstarch which has been rubbed to a smooth paste with a little cold water.
Allow to cook 15 minutes over hot water.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix all just before serving.

title: tomato-zucchini scallop
directions: Place half of zucchini slices in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with half of diced tomato, onions, croutons, salt and pepper. Repeat layers once; top with tomato wedges.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve immediately. Serves 6.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: Peel, quarter, core and boil squash in salted water until tender; drain.
Season with brown sugar and paprika.
Bake apple quarters in covered baking dish in a 325° oven with two tablespoons of butter or oleo.
Place 1/4 apples in each 1/4 squash.
Pour over each 1 teaspoon chutney.
Heat in 400° oven (1 squash and 1 apple = 4 servings).

title: zesty bake beans
directions: Place bacon in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole dish. Cover with paper toweling.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes. Remove paper towel and bacon.
Reserve drippings in casserole dish.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook onions in bacon drippings on High for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Microwave on High for 10 minutes, stirring twice.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Mix together apples, cranberries and sugar.
Melt margarine in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour fruit mixture in dish.
Combine remaining ingredients with hand.

Sprinkle on top of first mixture. Bake 45 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven until bubbly or light brown, 45 minutes will probably be long enough, depending on your oven. This is very good at Christmastime.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in top of double boiler over hot water.
Stir in noodles and peanuts or coconut to coat thoroughly. Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: strawberry pretzel salad or dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, oleo and sugar (food processor is good to use). Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach (microwave).
To cooked spinach add diced artichokes, cubed cream cheese, Worcestershire, lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well. Put in baking dish. Cover with onion rings.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter or margarine in electric skillet at 250°.
Add brown sugar and mix thoroughly, spread evenly over bottom of skillet.
Arrange pineapple and nuts over sugar mixture.
Pour cake batter over fruit, spreading evenly.
Cover skillet with vent open and bake 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out dry.
Invert cake on serving plate while still warm.

title: chow chow
directions: Put tomatoes in pan of boiling water, then take out immediately.
Put tomatoes in a pan of cold water.
Peelings come off easily.
Discard peelings.
Cut tomatoes in large chunks.
Mix sugar, vinegar, chopped onions, chopped peppers and salt.
Blend well. Mix with tomatoes in large pan.
Cook on stove top for 2 1/2 hours over medium heat.

title: kool-aid play dough(not eatable)
directions: Mix flour, salt and cream of tartar in a bowl.
In a saucepan, combine Kool-Aid, oil and water.
Heat until boiling.
Add dry ingredients to Kool-Aid mixture.
Knead into play dough.
Keep in an airtight container.

title: grandma a's french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Refrigerate left over dressing.

title: candy apple salad
directions: Mix together pineapple, apple cider vinegar, flour, sugar and egg.
Put in saucepan and heat until thick.
Add cooled mixture to apples.
Then add Cool Whip and peanuts.
Mix well.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: zucchini in dill
directions: In saucepan combine zucchini, onion, water, salt, bouillon and dill weed.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer, covered 5 minutes.
Do not drain.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, salt and spices, then water with soda, then flour, then raisins and sliced apples to batter. Grease and flour baking pans.
Cook in slow oven at 325° to 350° until done.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Roll into 1 inch balls. Cook in pan on medium heat until done; drain on paper towels. These are good alone or in your favorite spaghetti sauce.
Also, very good in brown gravy.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Mix heated sweet potatoes, butter, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with Kraft Marshmallow Creme.
Bake at 350° until Marshmallow Creme browns.

title: shrimp salad
directions: In a large bowl, put lettuce, tomatoes, onions, eggs and shrimp.
Add macaroni; add enough mayonnaise to mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill about 1 hour.
Serve.

title: delicious potato rolls
directions: Crumble yeast and add 1/2 cup of the water.
Cream shortening and add sugar and salt.
Blend in potatoes and well beaten eggs, as well as the yeast.
Sift flour before measuring.
Add 1 cup of flour with the rest of the water.
Then work the rest of the flour in with spoon and hands (later); knead until smooth.
Let rise in a greased bowl until doubled in size.
Punch down, make into rolls and let rise until doubled in size in greased pan.
Or, cover tightly and store in refrigerator.
Then you may use it as needed. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: fruity breakfast parfait
directions: In glass, layer pineapple, raspberries, yogurt, banana and dates.
Sprinkle top with almonds.

title: seven-minute pudding
directions: In a microwave-safe mixing bowl, combine sugar and cornstarch. With a hand mixer, beat in milk and egg yolks until smooth. Microwave on Medium for 5 minutes.
Beat well with mixer. Microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour into serving dishes; cool.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake chicken in greased (buttered) pan until tender.
Cook the rice.
Add onion soup mix and butter to cooked rice.
Spread over chicken.
Bake in oven until browned.

title: cantonese fried rice
directions: Bring broth to a boil.
Add rice.
Cover and cook until rice is done.
In a large skillet, place the oil and egg; cut egg into strips as it cooks.
Add shrimp, chicken and pork, about 3/4 cup altogether.
Add cooked rice and season with salt, pepper, green onions and soy sauce.
Blend together and cook over low heat for 7 to 8 minutes.
Top with slivered almonds.

title: feta potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, feta, thyme, salt and pepper. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet over medium heat. Add potato mixture. Using pancake turner, press to form even later. Cook 10-12 minutes, or until golden. Reduce heat. Using large, flat plate, slide potato from skillet. Invert potato back into skillet and continue cooking other side 20 minutes, or until golden. Place on platter and garnish with thyme sprig.

title: rice chex dessert
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Spread half of mixture evenly in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish; pat down. Spread ice cream evenly over top.
Sprinkle remaining cereal mixture over ice cream; pat lightly.
Cover and freeze.
When ready to serve, remove from freezer and cut into squares.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: cranberry corn bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Beat eggs. Add to butter-sugar mixture. Add milk and mix well. Sift dry ingredients together and add gradually to liquid mixture. Fold in cranberries.
Pour batter into a 9-inch square pan. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until center springs back when pressed lightly.

title: cranberry fruit jello
directions: Mix jello following box directions, omitting 1/2 cup water. Grind cranberries, grapes, nuts and celery together.
Add sugar and mix.
Let sit a little while and then add to jello.
Pour into fancy dish or mold.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except egg whites.
Pour into 2 partially baked pie shells.
Bake in 325 degree oven until firm. Top with meringue made from egg whites and brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onions 5 minutes.
Combine everything except stuffing, butter and cheese.
Mix butter and stuffing in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle stuffing and cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: horseradish mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add vinegar and salt. When slightly set, fold in horseradish and whipped cream. Mold and chill.

title: tasty cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredient together. Roll in nuts or parsley to garnish. Place on plate in any shape.

title: squash casserole
directions: Stew squash until done.
Add all ingredients, except cheese. Bake in 350° oven until light brown.
Remove cover and top with grated cheese and let melt.
Serve hot.

title: tuna tot casserole(microwave)
directions: Combine green pepper, onion and oil in a 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook in microwave on High for 2 minutes or until green pepper and onion are tender.
Blend in soup, milk, mushrooms, tuna and peas.
Top with Tater Tots.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top of casserole and microwave for 1 to 2 minutes or until melted.

title: butch's sausage dip
directions: Brown the sausage, drain and pat dry, then add the onion, Rotel tomatoes, black olives and simmer till all the juice is gone, also add a little Tabasco or Crystal hot sauce (to taste), then add cream cheese (cubed) until melted, and serve with corn chips, scoops, crackers, etc.
The spicier the sausage and tomatoes, the spicier the dip.
Great reheated, too.

title: quick and easy fish soup
directions: Cook and stir onion, garlic and thyme in oil in Dutch oven until onion is tender.
Add broth, crushed red pepper, water, potatoes and carrots.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add fish and green pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat, cover and simmer until fish flakes easily with fork, about 5 minutes.

title: creamed new potatoes with parmesan
directions: In a large saucepan, boil new potatoes in water just until tender;
drain and keep warm.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Pour 1/4 cup
water in small bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over it; let set.
Pour milk and 3 cups water in large mixing bowl. Stir in sugar and salt.
Then stir yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Stir sifted flour in bowl until it is the right consistency.
Add shortening and stir.
Place dough on floured board and knead. Place in greased Dutch oven, turning over so the top is greased. Let rise 1 hour and 45 minutes or until double in bulk.
Punch down and rise 1 more hour.
Make into biscuits; place in baking pan.
Let rise 1 hour or until doubled.
Bake in 425° oven until browned.
To raise the dough, place dish towel over top of pan. Place it on oven rack with a pan of hot water underneath.

title: chicken stew
directions: Combine chicken, sausage, onion and celery.
Cook until chicken falls off bone.
Debone and return to broth (2 to 3 cups). Add margarine, salt, pepper and rice.
Cook until rice is plumped.
Add cream of chicken soup; simmer for 20 minutes or until thickened.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook sugar and butter, stirring constantly.
The mixture will separate, when it comes back together stir in slivered almonds. Continue cooking over low heat until candy comes together and is dark brown.
Pour into 2 buttered cookie sheets.
When hard but still warm, spread with chocolate and sprinkle ground almonds on top.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over sliced cucumbers and onions; let stand 2 hours, then drain off water. Combine sugar and vinegar; pour over cucumbers. Let stand 10 minutes; stir and place cucumbers into freezer containers. Keep frozen at least 2 days before eating. Thaw at room temperature, then keep refrigerated. Pickles will keep in the freezer for a year.

title: sour cream salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend until creamy and green, then add lots of blue cheese.
Then "flash" blend, leaving small chunks of Blue cheese.
Yields approximately 2 1/2 cups.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook cauliflower, covered, in 1/2 cup broth for 5 to 8 minutes. Do not drain.
Process in blender until smooth.
Cook broccoli, covered, in remaining broth with mustard seed and dill weed for 5 to 8 minutes.
Do not drain.
Process in blender.
Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk. Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add cauliflower, broccoli and cheese to sauce.
Cook and stir until just heated through and cheese is melted.

title: potato salad
directions: In a saucepan, bring to boil the sugar and vinegar. In a mixing bowl, beat well the eggs and mustard. Pour hot liquid to egg mixture and beat quickly and rapidly to keep from curdling. Remove potatoes and drain. Add to them the onion, pickles or pickle relish, celery seed and salad dressing. Pour in hot dressing and mix well. Cool before serving or can be eaten hot.

title: hopping john
directions: Add chopped RoTel tomatoes with juice to the onion and celery.
Add bacon and rice.
Mix all with peas.
Pour into 4 qt. casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: tender beef tips
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces. Cut off excess fat.
Pour soup over meat (do not dilute). Put in covered pan and bake for 5 hours at 225° or put in crock-pot on low for 7 or 8 hours. Can be served over mashed potatoes, rice or noodles.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar well.
Blend in chocolate.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat for 5 minutes after each egg is added.
Pour in cooled pie shell.
Refrigerate; chill until set
(for several hours).

title: peggy's barbecue
directions: Cook meat in crock-pot.
Take out and shred.
Put back in crock-pot and add sauce after you make it.

title: cheese cake
directions: Roll out graham crackers and mix with butter.
Line pan with mixture.
(Save enough for a thin layer of crumbs on top.)
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: grits n' cheese casserole
directions: Melt cheese and margarine in cooked grits.
Add milk, eggs and salt.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Delicious served with country ham.

title: baked beans
directions: Blend all ingredients, and bake at 375° until vegetables are tender.

title: apricot unbeatables
directions: Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and egg whites.
Add walnuts and apricots; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto well-greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes, depending on size.
Cool on rack.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Mix in order given; roll in balls, press down and sprinkle with sugar and bake.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, butter, soda and sugar.
In an oblong pan, spread 1/2 of mixture.
Pat lightly.
Spread pie filling over first layer, then spread remaining mixture over pie filling.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter and pour over oatmeal.
Add sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add egg, vanilla and pecans.
Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Drop small amount (1/2 teaspoon) of mixture on cookie sheet, not too close.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° (look at in 8 minutes). Let cool on foil.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: dry jerk seasoning
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Store leftovers in tightly sealed glass jar.
This jerk seasoning mix will retain pungency for about one month.
Makes 5 tablespoons of seasoning at 19 calories per serving.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets. Peel and slice. Toss potatoes, onion, celery, eggs, pickles, olives, sugar and salt and pepper.
Mix in Miracle Whip. Serves 10.

title: chicken ritz
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and place on top.
Melt the oleo and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables in quart jar.
Combine remaining ingredients in a separate jar.
Shake vinegar to blend.
Pour over vegetables 4 hours or overnight.
Shake jar several times to coat top of veggies with marinade.

title: chocolate torte
directions: You will need a trifle bowl.

title: salmon delight
directions: Blend all ingredients except salmon. Add salmon and mix well. Serve on crisp lettuce with wheat crackers.

title: snails
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix margarine, garlic, parsley, onion, salt and pepper.
Spoon small amount of margarine mixture into each snail shell; insert snail and top each with remaining margarine mixture.
Pour wine into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish or into each section of snail plates; arrange filled shells open end up on dish or plates.
Bake until margarine mixture is bubbly, about 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and stir in 2 packages partially thawed strawberries.
Set aside.
Cream 3 tablespoons brown sugar and margarine.
Stir in pretzels.
Press mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Blend in bowl cream cheese, scant cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread cheese mixture over cooled pretzel crust.
Add strawberry mixture and refrigerate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel, slice and boil potatoes for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Mix soup, sour cream and onions until smooth.
Layer potatoes, then soup mix and potatoes with soup mix on top in a casserole dish.

title: orange dessert
directions: Mix and save 1/2 cup mixture for topping. Place remaining mixture in bottom of 9 x 13 glass dish for crust.

title: cherry dream squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 13 X 9 pan. Combine cake mix, 6 Tablespoons margarine and 1 cup of the rolled oats. Mix until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping. To remaining crumbs, add egg and mix until well blended. Press into prepared pan. Pour cherry pie filling over crust, spread to cover. To reserved crumbs, add remaining 1/4 cup oats, margarine, nuts and brown sugar. Beat until mixed well. Sprinkle over cherry mixture. Bake 30 to 40 minutes. Cool completely.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil, drain and blanch macaroni.
Drain peas.
Quarter eggs, then slice in two.
Slice onions and cover with 1/2 cup salad oil, 1/2 cup vinegar, salt and paprika.
Mix together.

title: zesty lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a Ziploc Baggie with lemon juice and refrigerate overnight.

title: cheesy meat dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage and hamburger; mix all ingredients together in crock-pot and heat thoroughly.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet; drain.
Add salt, pepper, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce and catsup; then tomatoes, corn and beans.
Cook all together about 5 minutes.
Pour into large baking dish and top with cornbread batter. Bake at 400°until cornbread is done.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an airtight container. To serve, place 3 tablespoons mix in a cup.
Add 3/4 cup boiling water; mix well.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until smooth.
Mash bananas and mix together with sugar and shortening mix.
Add eggs, flour, salt and soda and mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend thoroughly and pour into 2 prepared 9-inch pie shells. Bake at 350° until set.

title: creamy scrambled eggs
directions: In a small saucepan, melt 1 tablespoon butter.
Add flour and cook; stir for a minute.
Stir in sour cream and cook for a minute on low heat; set aside.
Beat together eggs, salt and pepper.
In a large skillet, melt remaining butter.
Pour in eggs and cook slowly until just set and still quite moist on top.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream mixture and mix well.
Turn heat to lowest setting so as not to cook eggs any longer.
May be made up to 1 hour ahead.
Serves 8.

title: shovel steak
directions: Cut rump or round steak, sliced thin.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fry in oil or butter until brown.
Remove from skillet. Add more oil and saute a generous amount of thinly sliced onions until golden brown.
In casserole dish, place layer of meat and onions; sprinkle with generous amounts of flour and brown sugar. Add more meat, onions, flour and brown sugar.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Add tomato paste and 1 quart of beer or enough to cover.
Bring liquid to boil and bake until tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind zucchini squash and onions.
Add 5 tablespoons of salt and let set overnight.
Drain in the morning and rinse in cold water.
Add vinegar, sugar, nutmeg, dry mustard, turmeric and pepper.
Grind green and red pepper and add to mixture.
Cook 3 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: caramel dip
directions: Beat cream cheese in a mixing bowl at medium speed of an electric mixer until creamy.
Add caramel sauce and mix well. Spoon into a serving bowl.
Serve at room temperature with apple slices or pretzels.
Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: Fry the mushrooms and onions in the butter until cooked. Spread in the pie shell.
Add the Swiss cheese.
Beat the eggs and milk together and pour over the mushrooms and cheese in the pie shell.
Add salt and pepper, if desired.
Top with the Parmesan cheese and crumbled bacon.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Place melted margarine in an ungreased 9-inch pan.
Over this, place the crumbs in 1 layer, followed by the coconut and chocolate chips.
Do not stir.
Over this pour the milk.
Do not stir.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: extra good buns
directions: When scalded milk reaches lukewarm, add yeast, sugar and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Mix.
When bubbly, add salt, eggs, oil and remaining flour.
Knead.
Let rise in warm place until double.
Make into buns on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise and bake 20 minutes in 300° oven.
Makes about 15 buns.

title: 5-minute toasty burgers
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Mix meat and onion; spread on toast slices, making sure mixture covers edges.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place, meat side up, on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 3 to 5 minutes, or until meat is done. To serve, cut slices in half.
Makes 20 half-slice servings.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg, then beat in remaining ingredients.
Grease griddle with 3 tablespoons butter for each pancake.
Keep hot on hot plate with paper towels.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water.
Place in a large bowl.
Add sugar and melted shortening; mix.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Melt another 1/4 cup of shortening or margarine in a bread pan.

title: martha's jambalaya
directions: Cut sausage into rounds or crumble if using bulk sausage. Brown in large Dutch oven (8 quarts or more) or ovenproof pan with tight-fitting lid.
Drain all but about 1/4 cup fat.
To the fat add the onions, pepper and garlic and saute until soft, but not brown.
Add rice and saute lightly.
Add tomato sauce, the 3 cups water, the sausage and spices.
Mix well.
Bring to simmer, cover and place in 350° oven for about 25 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed and rice is cooked.
Add more water if necessary, but do not stir until the rice is cooked.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown sausage; cool and drain.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt, cheese and mustard.
Beat again.
Add crumbled toast and sausage and stir.
Pour into pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pepperoni salad
directions: In large salad bowl, combine lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, garbanzo beans, pepperoni, and onion.
Pour Italian dressing over. Toss lightly.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Yields 8 or 9 servings.

title: fresh pork with vegetables
directions: Simmer pork for 45 minutes.
Add vegetables and salt and cook for 45 minutes longer or until tender.
Cut pork in thin slices and vegetables, except cabbage, into thin strips.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat egg into milk and add all remaining ingredients.
Bake at 450° in 8-inch buttered pan for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spicy meat balls
directions: About 2 hours before serving:
In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in 1 tablespoon olive or salad oil, cook half of chopped onions, stirring occasionally, until tender and golden. Set aside.
Remove sausage from casings.
In medium bowl, mix sausage meat, ground beef, cooked onions, bread crumbs, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper just until blended.
With hands, shape mixture into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Brown meatballs until golden.
In large saucepan over medium to high heat, add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 10 minutes, then add meat balls.
Cook for about 1 hour until sauce thickens.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers, onions and celery and place in a crock and cover with boiling water to scald.
Let stand in water for 4 minutes.
Drain this water off and pour peppers into a large heavy cooking container.
Add the remainder of the ingredients.

title: strawberry slush salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
About 10 minutes before serving time, cut in squares and place on plates.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, chicken, chilies, sour cream and onions; heat in a pan.
Heat oil; cook tortillas until soft.
Spoon soup mixture into tortilla roll and place in a dish.
Cover with remaining soup mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Chill dough.
Drop by teaspoonful into powdered sugar.
Roll into small balls and flatten slightly.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly; drain on paper bag.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into loaf pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: mayonnaise
directions: All ingredients must be cold.
Add salt and vinegar to egg yolks and beat well.
Add oil slowly, beating constantly, until all of oil has been added.
Keep refrigerated.
Use in place of regular mayonnaise.

title: cheese balls
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and pineapple together.
Set 1 cup pecans aside.
Mix all remaining ingredients with cream cheese mixture.
Roll into balls or logs.
Refrigerate overnight. Remove.
Roll in 1 cup pecans.
Top with cherries or olives, if desired.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift dry ingredients.
With mixer, cream butter and brown sugar; beat well.
Add egg and molasses; beat until light in color.
On low speed, gradually add dry ingredients. Refrigerate dough 10 to 15 minutes.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: In a deep, heat-resistant nonmetallic casserole, combine all ingredients.
Heat, uncovered, in microwave oven for 8 minutes, or until mixture boils.
Stir mixture occasionally during last 3 minutes of cooking time.
Serve either hot or chilled.

title: hawaiian ham
directions: Melt butter or margarine in an electric skillet or wok.
Stir in garlic powder, soy sauce, brown sugar and orange juice.
Drain juice from canned pineapple and measure out 1 cup.
Add to skillet.
Heat until simmering, then add ham, pineapple and peas. Simmer for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serve alone or over rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Remove from bones
and
cut into pieces.
Mix
the	soup
with the sour cream
and	pour
over chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers; combine with
poppy
seed
and sprinkle over top soup mixture.
Melt oleo; pour
over top and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: oat nut bran muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add cereals, raisins and nuts.
Combine milk, eggs, oil, water and applesauce.
Stir liquid mixture with dry mixture only until moist.
Fill greased muffin tin 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Batter may be kept from 4 to 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: raspberry rhapsody
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until frothy.

title: frozen strawberry squares
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, nuts and butter.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven. Stir occasionally.
Reserve 1/3 of crumbs.
Pat rest in pan and cool.

title: skillet stuffing
directions: In a bowl combine first 4 ingredients; set aside - saute celery and onion in butter or margarine till tender. Add the corn bread mixture and seasonings - mix well and cook over medium heat until lightly browned. Yields 2 servings. (Can be doubled)

title: pina colada dip
directions: Serve with fresh pineapple and/or strawberries.

title: meat loaf(meat loaf for 50)
directions: In a large bowl or roasting pan thoroughly mix all ingredients. Shape into loaf pans, about seven loaves. Bake 15 minutes at 425°. Reduce heat to 350° continue 45 minutes or until brown. You can top this with ketchup or barbecue sauce.

title: tuna supreme
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add salt and pepper; mix. Add flour and blend to make a paste.
Stir in 1 cup milk and 1 can tuna.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Add second cup of milk and second can of tuna.
Reduce heat and simmer until thickened.
Serve over toasted light bread or garlic bread.

title: low-fat georgian chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Take off skin and cut into serving pieces.
Saute chicken on both sides.
Set chicken aside.
Add chopped onion to skillet and brown.
Add tomato paste, vinegar, wine, chicken broth, bay leaf, salt and pepper and bring to boil. Add chicken.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add more broth if necessary.
Sprinkle with parsley or dill and serve with lemon slices on cooked rice.

title: baked scallops
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole and sprinkle with 1 cup buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with bacon and olives.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. Can do ahead. Serves approximately 12.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Add hominy and tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add chili powder and cook until thick.
Put 1/2 in casserole.
Sprinkle 1/2 cheese and onion, then add remainder of hominy, cheese and onion.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl and mix well.
Dollop on broiled steaks or pass separately.
Yields 1/2 cup.

title: sweet-sour beef stew
directions: In 3 qt. saucepan, brown meat in hot oil.
Then add carrots, onion, tomato sauce, water, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, and salt.
Cover and cook over low heat until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Then to a tablespoon of cold water, add 2 teaspoons of cornstarch, add to stew.
Cook until thickened. Serve over noodles or rice.
Sprinkle with poppy seeds (optional).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine all wet ingredients separately.
Put nuts and raisins aside.
Slowly mix dry and wet ingredients until well blended.
Add nuts and raisins.
Spread in well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: In a greased baking pan, place chicken; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place sauerkraut over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Pour salad dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 325° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, green pepper, leeks, carrots, clam juice and broth in large pan. Bring to boiling. Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes. Place half of vegetable liquid mixture in bowl of blender. Cover and process until pureed. Blend in tomato paste and seasonings. Combine yogurt and flour. Stir a small amount of pureed mixture into yogurt. Combine yogurt mixture with remaining vegetable mixture. Stir in remaining mixture and shrimp. Heat through, but do not boil. Serve with oyster crackers.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut bread into cubes.
Mix all ingredients in baking dish. Bake at 350° until golden brown on top.

title: oatmeal cookie mix
directions: Put sugars, flour, salt, soda and baking powder through a coarse sieve.
Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Add rolled oats and mix well.
Store in cool place.

title: all-season grilled chicken
directions: Mix chili sauce, vinegar, horseradish, garlic and salt in a bowl. Reserve 1/2 of the marinade. Add chicken to bowl; turn to coat. Cover and marinate in the refrigerator for 5 minutes.

title: amalgamation cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar well.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix together flour and milk with the Crisco and sugar mixture, making sure to alternate flour and milk, beginning with flour and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 300°.

title: braised caraway pork chops
directions: On rack in broiling pan, broil chops, turning once until rare.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and milk; roll nuts, dates and candy that has been cut into small pieces in flour and then add coconut.
Cook in well greased tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: carob brownies
directions: Melt together butter and carob powder.
Beat until foamy eggs, salt, vanilla, sugar and dry milk.
Add to butter mixture, then stir in 1 cup carob powder until just mixed.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° until done.

title: orange crunch muffins
directions: Mix dry and then wet ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix 1 egg, margarine and lemon cake mix.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan (mixture will be dry).
In separate bowl, mix the cream cheese, 2 eggs and all but 1/4 cup of the powdered sugar.
Pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar after completely cooled; cut into small squares.

title: congealed salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and serve chilled.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish with rolls.
Cover with sausage and one half of cheese.
Mix eggs with soup and pour over mixture. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ambrosia mold salad
directions: Drain pineapple, add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup. Stir boiling water into jello and stir until completely dissolved. Stir in measured water/juice.
Chill until slightly thickened (approximately 1 1/2 hours).
Stir in whipped topping until smooth. Chill 1/2 hour.
Stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut.
Spoon into 6 cup mold.
Chill until firm (about 3 hours or overnight).
Unmold carefully.
Pretty and refreshing!

title: waldorf astoria red chocolate cake(red velvet cake)
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time. Mix well. Make a thin paste of the cocoa and food coloring. Add to creamed mixture. Sift flour and salt together. Add flour mixture and buttermilk to creamed mixture, one tablespoon at a time, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix soda and vinegar. Blend into mixture last.
Grease and flour three 8-inch pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Remove and cool.

title: moist and easy cake
directions: Put ingredients in a bowl as given and mix well with a wooden spoon.
Bake in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken genoa
directions: Dip chicken breasts in Parmesan cheese, egg and cracker crumbs. Brown in 1/2 cup oil in skillet.
Arrange in baking dish in single layer.
Arrange 1 slice of 1/4-inch jack cheese on each breast. Adding oil to skillet if necessary, saute sliced fresh mushrooms until tender.
Add wine and saute slowly for 5 minutes.
Spoon mushrooms over chicken (not too much liquid).
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Reserve broth for later use.
Mix chicken (deboned), salt, pepper, lemon juice, mayonnaise, soup and onion together; leave in refrigerator overnight.
Pour remaining chicken broth over stuffing mix.
Place on chicken mixture.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine corn and oil in bowl; set aside.
Mix sugar, vinegar, onion, salt and celery seed.
Bring to a boil; simmer 2 minutes. Pour over corn mixture.
Cover and cool.
Refrigerate several hours.
Drain and serve.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix well Jell-O, hot water and cold water.
Then add lime juice and pineapple juice.
Chill well and pour into a large punch bowl. Just before serving, add 1 (2 liter) ginger ale.

title: goochies
directions: Line a large cookie sheet with tinfoil and spray lightly with Pam. Lay out graham crackers on pan. Cook butter, sugar and vanilla about 3 minutes and pour over crackers. Sprinkle nuts over top. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Let cool and break apart.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and butter in skillet until tender.
Add salt and black pepper, chicken and mushroom soup.
Stir in cooked broccoli, noodles and milk; mix well.
Add Mozzarella cheese; mix well.
Add 3/4 cup of Cheddar cheese and stir all together.
Pour in casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake at 350° in oven for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: quick crescent taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In frying pan, brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, water and olives.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: one step pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients into mixer at once. Beat at medium speed for 20 minutes. Bake in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour, starting from a cold oven.

title: cube steak and gravy
directions: Batter and brown cube steak in electric skillet.
Remove from pan.
Add 1 can mushroom soup and 1 can water or milk and simmer. Return steak to pan and simmer for 1 hour.

title: traditional corn pudding
directions: In a medium bowl, combine kernels with sugar, nutmeg and pepper.
Add eggs, mixing well.
Stir in milk.
Turn into buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Place casserole dish in a pan of water and bake in preheated slow oven at 325° until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour.

title: tina's jello surprise
directions: Mix hot water and raspberry Jell-O together.
Chill until half set.
Pour heavy cream into small container and whip with the half-set Jell-O.
Pour into mold.
Set all the way.

title: wedding punch
directions: *Strawberry for pink, cherry for red, lemon-lime for green and lemon for yellow.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Butter pan and sprinkle dry, uncooked rice in bottom of pan. Salt and pepper chicken and place over rice.
Pour the onion and chicken soup over the chicken and about 1 can of water.
Place, uncovered, in 350° oven for about 3 minutes.
Cover and cook until done and brown, about 1 hour.

title: blackberry jam
directions: Wash and drain berries.
Put into blender; mash well.
Add 2 cups sugar.
Let come to boil.
Add 4 cups sugar and boil 20 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: crabmeat and sherry soup
directions: Combine soups, okra and crabmeat.
Heat together in top of double boiler; adding water if necessary to thin.
Add sherry just before serving.

title: meatballs rellenos
directions: Combine beef, chips, 1/3 cup picante sauce, egg, cilantro (reserving just a bit) and 1/4 teaspoon cumin and mix well.
Slice cheese into 12 cubes.
Dividing beef mixture into 12 equal portions and form into a meatball around a cube of cheese.
Place on a shallow rimmed baking sheet that has been lined with aluminum foil and bake meatballs 16 minutes at 450°.

title: annie's sherry pralines
directions: Cook sugar, sherry and half and half to soft ball (236°) stage when dropped in cold water. Remove from heat; add butter and pecans. Cool for 10 to 15 minutes; beat until mixture begins to thicken. Drop by tablespoon onto buttered wax paper or foil. If mixture gets too thick to drop before all is spooned out, set over blaze just until it is soft enough to drop.

title: pork curry
directions: In a large skillet, cook pork in oil until golden brown (sprinkle with salt); set aside.
Add apples, onion and garlic and cook until onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, raisins, brown sugar, vinegar, curry powder, ginger and 1 teaspoon salt.
Return pork to skillet.
Cover and simmer until pork is tender, basting occasionally.
Serve over rice. (Very good if you like curry.)

title: oliebollen(dutch holiday dessert)
directions: Dissolve yeast in deep bowl in 3 tablespoons lukewarm milk.
In another bowl, put flour.
Stir in egg, one at a time with wooden spoon.
Add rest of milk, slowly.
Add sugar raisins, orange and lemon peels.
Add this mixture to yeast and stir.
Cover with cloth and rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Add salt, then deep fry a tablespoon at a time; drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Beat egg yolks into milk and stir into dry mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly over low to medium heat.
(Note:
You will have lumps if not very careful.)
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in 2 tablespoons margarine and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cool.

title: broiled flounder scampi
directions: Place fillets in broiler pan.
Spoon garlic over fillets. Drizzle melted butter, lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste. Broil until lightly brown being careful not to overcook.
Fish should flake with fork.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add remaining ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool before slicing.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown the meat. Add the next 5 ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes. Combine the cheese mix, eggs, Parmesan cheese, pepper and parsley.
Place 1/2 the noodles in
a 9 x 13-inch pan, 1/2 cheese mixture, then 1/2 Mozzarella, then 1/2 meat sauce. Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: oven fried okra
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper, stir well. Put into plastic bag with okra and shake until coated. Spread oil in a 15 x 10 x 1 inch pan, spread okra evenly in pan.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring often.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until yolks and whites are blended. Add sugar, salt, nutmeg, and vanilla. Mix thoroughly. Add milk slowly stirring constantly. Pour into pastry lined pie pan. Bake in hot oven at 400
until inverted knife comes out clean.

title: aunt sadie's jam bars
directions: Bottom Layer:
Cream the butter with the sugar.
Blend in the egg yolks, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Using heel of hand, fit dough into bottom of a 10 x 12-inch baking pan.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook the diced rhubarb with the water and sugar until tender. Pour dry jello into large bowl.
Pour rhubarb mixture over jello and mix.
Add the orange juice; stir.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in the whipped topping; chill until set.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well with mixer and put in 3 bread loaf pans (greased and floured).
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes, then run knife around edges and turn out.
Can be wrapped and frozen.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add the vinegar.
Stir the oil in a little at a time, stirring well.

title: hot dog sauce by ralph
directions: Cook hamburg, onion and pepper together until very fine.
Add pepper, salt, paprika, garlic, oregano, chili powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Combine with hamburg mixture.
Add 3 cups water.
Simmer 3 hours.

title: lemon pie
directions: Stir together all ingredients and cook on slow fire until thickened.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put butter in pan and fry broccoli and onion in it.
Drain off excess butter.
Cook rice; put in onion and broccoli.
Put in 2/3 Cheez Whiz and soup; mix together.
Put in casserole dish.
Put remaining Cheez Whiz on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes until bubbly.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water, 1 1/2 cups cold water after dissolved.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and
pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 10 minutes in preheated 450° oven; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30
minutes
longer, or until filling is puffed in center and is well browned. Let pie cool before cutting.
Decorate top of
pie with
large
pecan
halves
before baking.
Serve with whipped cream or a large scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: lazy daizy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over uncooked oats.
Cover and let set for 20 minutes.
Beat oleo with sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add oats mixture to creamed mixture.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Pour in a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Don't remove from pan.
Cover with broiled icing.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas.
Blend well after each addition.
Stir in nuts. Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan. Cool on rack.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk slowly. Melt 1 stick margarine in deep pan.
Pour batter in middle of pan.
Drain fruit, cover batter with fruit and cook in oven at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: candied yams
directions: Wash
and pare potatoes; cut in wedges.
Place in a heavy pot with the remaining items and cook on high until potatoes are done (tender).
Watch carefully, the sugar will scorch easily.

title: salad
directions: Add the Jell-O to the Cool Whip.
Mix well and add the pineapple, oranges, cottage cheese and nuts.
Refrigerate and let set up.

title: chinese hamburger
directions: Brown meat, stirring to keep crumbly.
Add other ingredients (except chow mein noodles).
Mix well.
Bake in a greased casserole, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Top with chow mein noodles and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: low-fat banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in slow oven at 325° for about 1 hour.
Check with toothpick for doneness.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water; drain blueberries and pineapple (save the juice).
Measure out 1 cup of the juice and add to jello mixture.
Take pineapple and berries and add to mixture.
Place in refrigerator until congealed.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Blend together shortening, salt and sugar.
Add eggs, then applesauce, alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts, raisins and dates.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: mother's banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with sour milk; mix well.
Fold in mashed bananas.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can also be made as a layer cake.

title: swiss style scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, salt and pepper.
Blend butter and garlic salt and coat a 3-quart casserole generously.
Put in one layer of potatoes and one layer of mushrooms; sprinkle with cheese (reserve some for topping), parsley and onion.
Continue repeating layers until all ingredients are used.
Finish with layer of potatoes. Pour cream all over; sprinkle with cheese and bits of butter. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Serves 8.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Peel the avocados and mash the pulp into a bowl.
Add lemon juice, salt, garlic salt and cayenne pepper.
Add chopped onions, chopped green chilies and diced tomatoes.
Let set for 30 minutes. Place an avocado seed in the guacamole while setting or saving to prevent the salad from turning dark.

title: penney's squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cracker crumbs.
Pour into casserole dish and top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tuna dip
directions: Drain tuna and grind with fork until "fine".
Blend with cream cheese and mayonnaise until thoroughly combined.
Stir in ginger and lemon juice.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with tomatoes and toast or other accompaniments.

title: whoppers
directions: Melt margarine. Blend in sugars, eggs, and peanut butter. Mix in rest of ingredients. Mixture will be sticky. Shape into balls, flatten slightly. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 6 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: orange-cinnamon french toast
directions: In a bowl, combine butter, honey and cinnamon. Pour into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Spread to coat bottom of pan.

title: best-ever banana bread
directions: In large bowl stir flour, sugar, soda and salt.
In another bowl combine eggs, bananas, oil, milk and vanilla.
Stir just until combined.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until bread is done. Yields 1 loaf.

title: triple bean salad
directions: Rinse beans in cold water and drain.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: carrot sheet cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in greased sheet tin at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in a saucepan over low heat.
When mixture comes to a boil, add the remaining ingredients. Drop by tablespoon on wax paper to cool.

title: easy chicken parmesan
directions: Mix bread crumbs and cheese well. Dry chicken; dip in butter, then roll in cheese and bread crumbs. Cook at 350° until chicken is done, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: grandma's monkey bread
directions: Pour 1/2 melted margarine in a tube pan.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Roll each piece in cinnamon and sugar mixture and arrange in tube pan.
Pour remaining ingredients over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tangy apple slaw
directions: Core and dice apples.
Toss apples, raisins, cabbage, celery and bell peppers.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix with salad.
Makes six servings.

title: jelly roll cake
directions: Beat eggs about 3 minutes.
Add sugar and beat until thick. Slowly add flour until combined. Line the bottom of a 15 1/2 x 101/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with waxed paper.
Now spread the dough evenly over waxed paper and bake 9 minutes at 400° until surface springs back when touched.

title: furniture polish
directions: Mix the warm water, vinegar and oil.
Wash furniture off with cloth saturated with the polish.
Wipe dry with a soft dry cloth.

title: chocolate cherry cremes
directions: Stir together chocolate chips and milk in a 2-quart heavy saucepan over low heat until chips melt. Remove from heat. Stir in sugar, nuts and cherries until well mixed. Chill mixture until cool enough to handle. Roll by teaspoonfuls into balls and then into coconut. Chill until firm, approximately 4 hours. Keep cold. Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, stalk of celery and onion in 1 to 2 cups of water; debone chicken.
Mix crumbled crackers, butter and poppy seed and put half in bottom of pan (use large pan).
Put a mixture of chicken, soups and broth over crackers, then top with the other half of crumbs.
Bake until bubbly and brown.
Can be cut in halves or thirds.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and spoon into a 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Pour peas and carrots over top.
Slice eggs over top.

title: "baklava"
directions: Grind nuts fine and mix with sugar and spices.
Grease 11 x 16-inch pan (not a cookie sheet) with butter.
Place 4 sheets of filo into pan.
Brush each sheet with butter.
Sprinkle with nuts thinly.
Cover with 3 sheets of filo, brushing each with butter. Add mixture of nuts again as before.
Repeat this until all nuts are used.
End with 3 sheets of filo on top.
Brush with final butter.
Slice the entire thing into diamond shapes to aid in baking.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Place in oven.
Cook for 1 hour, until lightly brown.
Remove from oven.
Let cool.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Cut up tomatoes.
Combine lettuce, cheese, onions, olives and tomatoes.
Into meat, stir tomato liquid, bean dip, chili powder and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add to lettuce mixture; toss well.
Top with chips.
Serve at once.
Makes 2 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups (2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch) or line with paper baking cups.
Beat egg slightly in medium bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients except blueberries until just moistened.
Fold berries into batter. Divide batter evenly among cups.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.

title: deviled crab meat casserole
directions: Combine milk and soft bread crumbs.
Gently stir in crab meat and finely sliced whites of hard-boiled eggs.
Mash the egg yolks, along with salt, dry mustard, red pepper and melted butter.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs. Bake in 425° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, 2 teaspoons salt, margarine, egg and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover bowl tightly with aluminum foil. Refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.

title: company cheesecake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; press on bottom and 2/3 of sides of 9-inch pan.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion; drain.
Heat mushroom soup, Milnot and chilies.
Layer bottom of large casserole with tortillas (about 1 1/2 cups).
Cover them with 1/2 meat and onions and then cheese.
Add remaining meat and then soup mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, or in microwave, until cheese melts and mixture is bubbly.
Serve with extra tortillas.
(To rush, 1/2 cheese can be melted in soup mixture.)

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; cool to lukewarm. Put yeast in 1/4 cup water. Add 1 teaspoon sugar. Combine mixtures, beaten eggs and 4 cups flour. Beat thoroughly, then add 4 cups flour. Do not knead. Cover and put in refrigerator. Cut off uniform size pieces of dough. Let molded rolls rise in a warm place about 1 hour or until dough doubles in size.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix and put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Crush 1 1/2 tubes Ritz crackers and mix with 1 stick melted margarine.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cinnamon apple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and candy in boiling water.
Stir in applesauce, lemon juice and salt.
Pour into 5-cup mold and chill. Serves 10 to 12.

title: spinach dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all together and place in White Mountain bread from Publix Danish Bakery, unsliced.
Cut hole in top.
Peel out dough.
Place dip in hole.

title: mulled grape juice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks before serving.
Makes 5 cups.

title: pete's camp peas
directions: Place in crock-pot on low to medium heat; cook until peas are done.
Excellent with cornbread or rice.

title: baked ham
directions: Put ham in pan and drain juice over ham.
Layer pineapple on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apricot frappe
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Crush graham crackers with butter and 1/4 cup sugar.
Press in pie tin.

title: rice and beef casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions and set aside.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients. Season to taste with the remaining ingredients.

title: crab quiche
directions: Saute mushrooms.
Sprinkle cheese into pie shell.
Beat eggs with milk and seasonings; pour over cheese.
Sprinkle crab and mushrooms over pie.
Bake at 370° for 35 minutes or until firm in the middle.
Serves 4.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: milnot cheesecake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add pineapple.
Add gelatin and blend well.
In large cold bowl, whip Milnot until stiff.
Fold Milnot into gelatin mixture.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted oleo.
Pack 2/3 of crumb mixture on bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add filling and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill overnight.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: pork roast la soy
directions: Dry roast with paper towel.
Place, fat side up, on roasting rack in roasting pan.
Roast in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes per pound or until done.
Baste with soy sauce after 1 hour and 30 minutes of baking.
Mix remaining soy sauce with syrup.
Cover roast with mixture 10 minutes before removing from oven.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Slice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hollywood trail mix
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a large bowl, combine oats, nuts and spices.
Add oil, honey and water and stir until moistened.
Spread on an oiled jelly roll pan.
Bake until golden, about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Stir in apricots, prunes, apples and raisins.
Refrigerate in a covered jar.
Makes 8 cups.

title: lemonade fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss well.
Chill salad before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh apple bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil well.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add the flour mixture to the egg mixture and fold in apples and nuts.
Use slow speed on mixer.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool, then dust with sifted powdered sugar.
Cut into 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Cook popcorn.
Microwave margarine, brown sugar and corn syrup on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir, then microwave again on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Put popcorn in brown paper bag and roll down sides.
Pour caramel sauce over popcorn and stir until coated evenly.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Do this 3 times, stirring or shaking after each time.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; put in bottom of casserole dish and add a layer of Tater Tots.
Pour soup over all.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry cobbler(from the best blueberry picker, lori kelly.)
directions: Blend and place in a 3-quart buttered baking dish.

title: lemon puff pie
directions: In saucepan, combine pudding, sugar and 1/4 cup water.
Add 2 egg yolks and blend.
Add remaining 1 3/4 cups of water.
Cook until thick.
Add lemon juice.
Pour half of filling in baked 8-inch pie shell.
Beat egg whites and fold remaining half of filling into the whites while hot.
Chill.

title: pork and bean chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer.
Makes a really great chili that's fast and easy.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Cook and crumb bacon. Save 1/4 cup drippings. Add onions, sugar, mustard and vinegar. Cook until liquid is reduced to 1/3, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Mix all ingredients in 3-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix the herbs and spices together in a bowl.
Set aside.
Heat oil in nonstick skillet over low heat.
Add spice mixture.
Stir well.
Simmer 4 to 5 minutes to mellow the flavors. Put nuts in bowl and pour the spice mixture over them.
Toss well.
Spread nuts in single layer on baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Stir with wooden spoon once or twice.

title: caramel pie
directions: Melt 1 cup of sugar in a heavy pan or skillet and stir until all lumps are gone and it is completely liquid, but do not let it scorch.
Heat milk to scalding point but do not let it boil.
Add hot milk to caramelized sugar and cook until smooth.
Mix flour and remaining sugar and slowly beat into milk mixture.
Beat egg yolks and add slowly to mixture, beating constantly.
Add butter and cook until quite thick.
Add vanilla.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels with milk (1/3 cup).
Stir frequently.
Mix rest of milk (1/3 cup) with cake mix.
Melt butter and add with nuts to cake mix.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place raw potatoes in a large baking dish.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and milk gradually.
Remove from heat and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Top with cheese at 30 minutes and cover until last 15 minutes.

title: stir-fry beef and snow peas
directions: In medium bowl, mix steak, sherry, soy sauce and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Dissolve remaining 1 tablespoon cornstarch in broth and reserve.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in large skillet.
Add beef and garlic; cook over high heat, stirring constantly, until browned, about 3 minutes.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add snow peas and bean sprouts.
Cover and simmer over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes.
Add beef broth mixture; cook and stir until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with walnuts.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: To prepare, melt butter and cheese over low heat, stirring often.
Sift together sugar and cocoa; pour cheese mixture over dry ingredients.
Mix with heavy duty mixer or by hand.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Pour into a 15 x 10-inch pan.
Chill; cut into pieces.
Makes 5 pounds.
